briHistPMOPTMinInitialize.description: Used to initialize the value of the briHistPMOPTMinValue object to 0.

briHistPMOPTMaxValue.name: briHistPMOPTMaxValue
briHistPMOPTMaxValue.description: The maximum optical power transmitted at the output of the transceiver.

briHistPMOPTMaxTimeStamp.name: briHistPMOPTMaxTimeStamp
briHistPMOPTMaxTimeStamp.description: The date and time stamp of the maximum optical power transmitted value.

briHistPMOPTMaxValidity.name: briHistPMOPTMaxValidity
briHistPMOPTMaxValidity.description: Indicates the validity of the provided maximum optical power transmitted value.

briHistPMOPTMaxInitialize.name: briHistPMOPTMaxInitialize
briHistPMOPTMaxInitialize.description: Used to initialize the value of the briHistPMOPTMaxValue object to 0.

briHistPMOPTAvgValue.name: briHistPMOPTAvgValue
briHistPMOPTAvgValue.description: The average optical power transmitted at the output of the transceiver.

briHistPMOPTAvgTimeStamp.name: briHistPMOPTAvgTimeStamp
briHistPMOPTAvgTimeStamp.description: The date and time stamp of the average optical power transmitted value.

briHistPMOPTAvgValidity.name: briHistPMOPTAvgValidity
briHistPMOPTAvgValidity.description: Indicates the validity of the provided average optical power transmitted value.

briHistPMOPTAvgInitialize.name: briHistPMOPTAvgInitialize
briHistPMOPTAvgInitialize.description: Used to initialize the value of the briHistPMOPTAvgValue object to 0.

cpCrntPMTable.name: cpCrntPMTable
cpCrntPMTable.description: A table of current performance monitoring statistics collected for the circuit packs on the NE.

cpCrntPMEntry.name: cpCrntPMEntry
cpCrntPMEntry.description: The row entry object of the equipment current performance monitoring table. Each row of this table contains a full set of PM statistics and related data for a current measurement interval for a given circuit pack.

cpCrntPMCpTypeIdx.name: cpCrntPMCpTypeIdx
cpCrntPMCpTypeIdx.description: The type of the circuit pack targeted for PM retrieval.

cpCrntPMShelfIdx.name: cpCrntPMShelfIdx
cpCrntPMShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the circuit pack targeted for PMs is provisioned.

cpCrntPMSlotIdx.name: cpCrntPMSlotIdx
cpCrntPMSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot within which the circuit pack targeted for PMs is provisioned.

cpCrntPMIntervalTypeIdx.name: cpCrntPMIntervalTypeIdx
cpCrntPMIntervalTypeIdx.description: The type of PM bin according to interval length.

cpCrntPMTempTimeStamp.name: cpCrntPMTempTimeStamp
cpCrntPMTempTimeStamp.description: The date and time stamp of the temperature value.

cpCrntPMTempValidity.name: cpCrntPMTempValidity
cpCrntPMTempValidity.description: Indicates the validity of the provided temperature value.

cpHistPMTable.name: cpHistPMTable
cpHistPMTable.description: A table of historical performance monitoring statistics collected for the circuit packs on the NE.

cpHistPMEntry.name: cpHistPMEntry
cpHistPMEntry.description: The row entry object of the circuit pack historical performance monitoring table. Each row of this table contains a full set of PM statistics and related data for a historical measurement interval for a given circuit pack.

cpHistPMCpTypeIdx.name: cpHistPMCpTypeIdx
cpHistPMCpTypeIdx.description: The type of the circuit pack targeted for PM retrieval.

cpHistPMShelfIdx.name: cpHistPMShelfIdx
cpHistPMShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the circuit pack targeted for PMs is provisioned.

cpHistPMSlotIdx.name: cpHistPMSlotIdx
cpHistPMSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot within which the circuit pack targeted for PMs is provisioned.

cpHistPMIntervalTypeIdx.name: cpHistPMIntervalTypeIdx
cpHistPMIntervalTypeIdx.description: The type of PM bin according to interval length.

cpHistPMIntervalIdx.name: cpHistPMIntervalIdx
cpHistPMIntervalIdx.description: The specific PM bin number. The range is 1..96 for 15-minute bins, and for 1-day historical bins, the value is 1.

cpHistPMTempTimeStamp.name: cpHistPMTempTimeStamp
cpHistPMTempTimeStamp.description: The date and time stamp of the temperature value.

cpHistPMTempValidity.name: cpHistPMTempValidity
cpHistPMTempValidity.description: Indicates the validity of the provided temperature value.

gcc0ConfigTable.name: gcc0ConfigTable
gcc0ConfigTable.description: A table of GCC0 configuration information. This table contains one row for every provisioned GCC0.

gcc0ConfigEntry.name: gcc0ConfigEntry
gcc0ConfigEntry.description: A conceptual row that contains GCC0 configuration information of an interface. Each instance must correspond to an instance of an OTN Port capable of supporting GCC. Instances of this conceptual row persist across agent restarts.

gcc0ConfigCpTypeIdx.name: gcc0ConfigCpTypeIdx
gcc0ConfigCpTypeIdx.description: The specific type of circuit pack provisioned.

gcc0ConfigShelfIdx.name: gcc0ConfigShelfIdx
gcc0ConfigShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the gcc0 is provisioned.

gcc0ConfigSlotIdx.name: gcc0ConfigSlotIdx
gcc0ConfigSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot in which the gcc0 is provisioned.

gcc0ConfigPortIdx.name: gcc0ConfigPortIdx
gcc0ConfigPortIdx.description: The number of the port on the circuit pack on which the gcc0 provisioned.

gcc0ConfigMode.name: gcc0ConfigMode
gcc0ConfigMode.description: The desired mode to which the gcc0 is to be provisioned.

gcc0ConfigAdminStatus.name: gcc0ConfigAdminStatus
gcc0ConfigAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the gcc.

gcc0ConfigOperStatus.name: gcc0ConfigOperStatus
gcc0ConfigOperStatus.description: The reported operational status of the gcc.

gcc0ConfigOperStatQlfr.name: gcc0ConfigOperStatQlfr
gcc0ConfigOperStatQlfr.description: A textual list of qualifiers of the reported operational status of the gcc.

gcc0ConfigRowStatus.name: gcc0ConfigRowStatus
gcc0ConfigRowStatus.description: This columnar object is used for creating and deleting a conceptual row of the gcc0 config table.

pvxL2IntfSubPortNumber.name: pvxL2IntfSubPortNumber
pvxL2IntfSubPortNumber.description: A number indentifying a entity smaller than and contained in a port. At this time, this value is unused and must be zero.

ipExtIntfPrimaryState.name: ipExtIntfPrimaryState
ipExtIntfPrimaryState.description: The reported operational status of the IP Interface.

ipExtIntfSecondaryState.name: ipExtIntfSecondaryState
ipExtIntfSecondaryState.description: A textual list of qualifiers for the reported operational status of the IP Interface

ipExtIntfNumberedStatus.name: ipExtIntfNumberedStatus
ipExtIntfNumberedStatus.description: Set to true if this is a numbered interface and false if it is unnumbered.

ipExtIntfAddressType.name: ipExtIntfAddressType
ipExtIntfAddressType.description: The type of addresses (v4/v6) used in this row of this MIB. Currently only ipv4 is allowed in this table.

ipExtIntfAddress.name: ipExtIntfAddress
ipExtIntfAddress.description: The IP Address associated with the interface.

ipExtIntfSubnetMask.name: ipExtIntfSubnetMask
ipExtIntfSubnetMask.description: The sub-net mask associated with the interface.

ipExtIntfMACAddr.name: ipExtIntfMACAddr
ipExtIntfMACAddr.description: The MAC address associated with the interface, if applicable. All zeros for a non-MAC interface.

ipExtIntfType.name: ipExtIntfType
ipExtIntfType.description: A value describing the type of interface.

ipExtIntfBroadcastAddress.name: ipExtIntfBroadcastAddress
ipExtIntfBroadcastAddress.description: The broadcast address associated with the interface.

ipExtIntfMode.name: ipExtIntfMode
ipExtIntfMode.description: Is the interface full or half-duplex?

ipExtIntfMTUSize.name: ipExtIntfMTUSize
ipExtIntfMTUSize.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit for the interface.

ipExtIntfGateway.name: ipExtIntfGateway
ipExtIntfGateway.description: The gateway IP address associated with the interface.

ipExtIntfRowStatus.name: ipExtIntfRowStatus
ipExtIntfRowStatus.description: This columnar object is used for creating and deleting a conceptual row of the ipExtIntf table.

condDateAndTime.name: condDateAndTime
condDateAndTime.description: This object is used in Trap messages to indicate the date and time at which the condition or alarm reported in the Trap message occurred.

condReportType.name: condReportType
condReportType.description: Indicates if this is a condition (non-alarmed) or an alarm. This object is used solely for reporting the condition report type in Trap messages.

condSeverity.name: condSeverity
condSeverity.description: Indicates the severity of the condition or alarm. This object is used solely for reporting the condition severity in Trap messages.

condServiceAffecting.name: condServiceAffecting
condServiceAffecting.description: Indicates if the presence of this active condition or alarm impacts the ability of the equipment to provide service as expected. This object is used solely for reporting whether or not a condition is service affecting in Trap messages.

condDescription.name: condDescription
condDescription.description: A textual decription of the condition or alarm. This object is used solely for reporting the condition description in Trap messages.

condObjectType.name: condObjectType
condObjectType.description: Identifies the type of managed object against which the condition or alarm is raised.

condCodeType.name: condCodeType
condCodeType.description: This object value uniquely identifies the type of condition or alarm that is raised.

actCondTable.name: actCondTable
actCondTable.description: This table lists all active conditions and alarms raised on the system.

actCondEntry.name: actCondEntry
actCondEntry.description: Contains identifying and descriptive attributes for a single active condition or alarm raised on the network element.

actCondNotifIdx.name: actCondNotifIdx
actCondNotifIdx.description: Identifies the type of condition or alarm that is active by pointing to the NOTIFICATION-TYPE object that corresponds to the raising event of the condition or alarm.

actCondTableEntryIdx.name: actCondTableEntryIdx
actCondTableEntryIdx.description: Identifies the type of resource that is alarmed by pointing to the corresponding table entry object.

actCondInstanceIdx.name: actCondInstanceIdx
actCondInstanceIdx.description: Identifies the specific instance of the idenitifed resource type that is alarmed by providing instance data that applies to an instance of the table entry object type identified by actCondTableEntryIdx. The instance data portion of the OID is mapped to an OCTET string.

actCondReportType.name: actCondReportType
actCondReportType.description: Indicates if the table entry is a condition (non-alarmed) or an alarm.

actCondDateAndTime.name: actCondDateAndTime
actCondDateAndTime.description: The date and time that the condition or alarm reported in the trap message was raised.

actCondSeverity.name: actCondSeverity
actCondSeverity.description: Indicates how severe the condition or alarm is.

actCondServiceAffecting.name: actCondServiceAffecting
actCondServiceAffecting.description: Indicates if the presence of this active condition or alarm impacts the ability of the equipment to provide service as expected.

actCondDescription.name: actCondDescription
actCondDescription.description: A textual decription of the condition or alarm.

actCondObjectType.name: actCondObjectType
actCondObjectType.description: Identifies the type of managed object against which the condition or alarm is raised.

actCondCodeType.name: actCondCodeType
actCondCodeType.description: This object value uniquely identifies the type of condition or alarm that is raised.

actCondSummary.name: actCondSummary
actCondSummary.description: This object summarizes the active alarm/condition status of the network element. The value of the object returned indicates the following status data: - noActiveConditions: there are no active alarms or conditions on the network element - nonAlarmedConditionsActive: there is one or more active conditions on the network element, but none are of alarmable severity - minorAlarmsActive: there is one or more active conditions and/or alarms on the network element, and the highest severity level alarm is minor - majorAlarmsActive: there is one or more active conditions and/or alarms on the network element, and the highest severity level alarm is major - criticalAlarmsActive: there is one or more active conditions and/or alarms on the network element, and the highest severity level alarm is critical

actAlarmTable.name: actAlarmTable
actAlarmTable.description: This table lists all active alarms raised on the system.

actAlarmEntry.name: actAlarmEntry
actAlarmEntry.description: Contains identifying and descriptive attributes for a single active alarm raised on the system.

actAlarmNotifIdx.name: actAlarmNotifIdx
actAlarmNotifIdx.description: Identifies the type of alarm that is active by pointing to the NOTIFICATION-TYPE object that corresponds to the raising event of the condition or alarm.

actAlarmTableEntryIdx.name: actAlarmTableEntryIdx
actAlarmTableEntryIdx.description: Identifies the type of resource that is alarmed by pointing to the corresponding table entry object.

actAlarmInstanceIdx.name: actAlarmInstanceIdx
actAlarmInstanceIdx.description: Identifies the specific instance of the idenitifed resource type that is alarmed by providing instance data that applies to an instance of the table entry object type identified by actAlarmTableEntryIdx. The instance data portion of the OID is mapped to an OCTET string.

actAlarmReportType.name: actAlarmReportType
actAlarmReportType.description: Indicates if the table entry is an alarm.

actAlarmDateAndTime.name: actAlarmDateAndTime
actAlarmDateAndTime.description: The date and time that the alarm reported in the trap message was raised.

actAlarmSeverity.name: actAlarmSeverity
actAlarmSeverity.description: Indicates how severe the alarm is.

actAlarmServiceAffecting.name: actAlarmServiceAffecting
actAlarmServiceAffecting.description: Indicates if the presence of this active alarm impacts the ability of the equipment to provide service as expected.

actAlarmDescription.name: actAlarmDescription
actAlarmDescription.description: A textual decription of the alarm.

actAlarmObjectType.name: actAlarmObjectType
actAlarmObjectType.description: Identifies the type of managed object against which the alarm is raised.

actAlarmCodeType.name: actAlarmCodeType
actAlarmCodeType.description: This object value uniquely identifies the type of alarm that is raised.

tl1UserTable.name: tl1UserTable
tl1UserTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned user that can operate the TL1 management interface on the NE. Each row contains a list of attributes that pertain to a provisioned TL1 user.

tl1UserEntry.name: tl1UserEntry
tl1UserEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the TL1 user table.

tl1UserIdx.name: tl1UserIdx
tl1UserIdx.description: This is the unique user identifier, or UID, that is used for TL1 access.

tl1IpLockoutAddr.name: tl1IpLockoutAddr
tl1IpLockoutAddr.description: This is an IP address from which TL1 user login attempts have been temporarily disabled due to an excessive number of failed user login attempts.

tl1LogTable.name: tl1LogTable
tl1LogTable.description: This table lists all the log entries generated by the TL1 interface on the BTI 7000 system.

tl1LogEntry.name: tl1LogEntry
tl1LogEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the TL1 log table.

tl1LogIdx.name: tl1LogIdx
tl1LogIdx.description: The unique identifier for this log entry. It is the global Log Id of the entry when viewed through the TL1 interface.

tl1LogSysName.name: tl1LogSysName
tl1LogSysName.description: The name of the BTI 7000 system at the time that the log was recorded.

tl1LogTypeSpecificLogNum.name: tl1LogTypeSpecificLogNum
tl1LogTypeSpecificLogNum.description: The type-specific number for this log.

tl1LogMsgCode.name: tl1LogMsgCode
tl1LogMsgCode.description: The message code that was issued for this log entry. This field is relevant to log entries for TL1 autonomous notifications. For example, the message code may be 'REPT ALM OC48'. A message code is reported for all log entries of type alarm, event and dbChange. For logs of type security or command, the message code is an empty string.

tl1LogDateAndTime.name: tl1LogDateAndTime
tl1LogDateAndTime.description: The timestamp of the log entry.

tl1LogMessage.name: tl1LogMessage
tl1LogMessage.description: This is the main log entry contents. The log entry is enclosed in double quotations.

latestTl1LogNum.name: latestTl1LogNum
latestTl1LogNum.description: Identifies the value of the tl1LogIdx object for the most recently added entry in the tl1LogTable.

snmpTrapRcvTable.name: snmpTrapRcvTable
snmpTrapRcvTable.description: This table contains one row for every configured SNMP trap receiver. Each row contains a list of attributes that pertain to a provisioned trap receiver. All access to this table, whether for read, write, or create requests are restricted to SNMP requests issued with a valid community string configured with read-write access.

snmpTrapRcvEntry.name: snmpTrapRcvEntry
snmpTrapRcvEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the SNMP trap receiver table.

snmpTrapRcvIdx.name: snmpTrapRcvIdx
snmpTrapRcvIdx.description: This string serves as a unique trap receiver Id and is used to index the table.

snmpTrapRcvIPAddr.name: snmpTrapRcvIPAddr
snmpTrapRcvIPAddr.description: The IP address of the trap receiver. The setting of this object is mandatory when creating a new row.

snmpTrapRcvPort.name: snmpTrapRcvPort
snmpTrapRcvPort.description: The port on the specified IP address of the trap receiver.

snmpTrapRcvNotifType.name: snmpTrapRcvNotifType
snmpTrapRcvNotifType.description: The type of notification service to be provided to the trap receiver. The notification type can be configured as inform only if the message version specified for the snmpTrapRcvVersion object is snmpv2c.

snmpTrapRcvVersion.name: snmpTrapRcvVersion
snmpTrapRcvVersion.description: The type of notification service to be provided to the trap receiver. The notification type can be configured as inform only if the message version specified for the snmpTrapRcvVersion object is snmpv2c. The setting of this object is mandatory when creating a new row.

snmpTrapRcvCommunity.name: snmpTrapRcvCommunity
snmpTrapRcvCommunity.description: The community string inserted into the trap messages generated for this trap receiver. The setting of this object is mandatory when creating a new row.

snmpTrapRcvTTL.name: snmpTrapRcvTTL
snmpTrapRcvTTL.description: The time-to-live for the trap receiver. When the trap receiver is created or this object is set, this object specifies how long the trap receiver is to be configured. When read, the value returned is the length of time remaining before the trap receiver is automatically deleted. The valid range for this object is 000-00 to 099-99. If this object is set to a value of 000-00, the trap receiver will never auto-delete.

snmpTrapRcvRowStatus.name: snmpTrapRcvRowStatus
snmpTrapRcvRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the SNMP trap receiver table.

xcvrXCTable.name: xcvrXCTable
xcvrXCTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned cross connection between optical transceiver facilities on wavelength translator, regenerator and manager circuit packs.

xcvrXCEntry.name: xcvrXCEntry
xcvrXCEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the optical transceiver cross connection table.

xcvrXCSrcTypeIdx.name: xcvrXCSrcTypeIdx
xcvrXCSrcTypeIdx.description: The specific type of wavelength conversion function of the transceiver port that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCSrcShelfIdx.name: xcvrXCSrcShelfIdx
xcvrXCSrcShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the transceiver port that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCSrcSlotIdx.name: xcvrXCSrcSlotIdx
xcvrXCSrcSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the transceiver port that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCSrcIdx.name: xcvrXCSrcIdx
xcvrXCSrcIdx.description: The number of the port of the transceiver port that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCDestTypeIdx.name: xcvrXCDestTypeIdx
xcvrXCDestTypeIdx.description: The specific type of wavelength conversion function of the transceiver port that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCDestShelfIdx.name: xcvrXCDestShelfIdx
xcvrXCDestShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the transceiver port that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCDestSlotIdx.name: xcvrXCDestSlotIdx
xcvrXCDestSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the transceiver port that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCDestIdx.name: xcvrXCDestIdx
xcvrXCDestIdx.description: The number of the port of the transceiver port that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

xcvrXCType.name: xcvrXCType
xcvrXCType.description: The type of cross connection between the identified source and destination transceiver ports. This is a mandatory object when a row of the transceiver cross connect table is created. Only 1-way and 2-way cross-connections are supported on optical transceiver ports

xcvrXCRowStatus.name: xcvrXCRowStatus
xcvrXCRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the transceiver cross connection table, which in turn controls the provisioning and de-provisioning of transceiver cross connections.

vcgXCTable.name: vcgXCTable
vcgXCTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned cross connection between VCGs on Muxponder circuit packs.

vcgXCEntry.name: vcgXCEntry
vcgXCEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the VCG cross connection table.

vcgXCSrcShelfIdx.name: vcgXCSrcShelfIdx
vcgXCSrcShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the VCG entity that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

vcgXCSrcSlotIdx.name: vcgXCSrcSlotIdx
vcgXCSrcSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the VCG entity that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

vcgXCSrcPortIdx.name: vcgXCSrcPortIdx
vcgXCSrcPortIdx.description: The number of the port of the VCG entity that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

vcgXCSrcIdx.name: vcgXCSrcIdx
vcgXCSrcIdx.description: The number of the VCG within the identified port that serves as the source port for the cross connection.

vcgXCDestShelfIdx.name: vcgXCDestShelfIdx
vcgXCDestShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the VCG entity that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

vcgXCDestSlotIdx.name: vcgXCDestSlotIdx
vcgXCDestSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the VCG entity that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

vcgXCDestPortIdx.name: vcgXCDestPortIdx
vcgXCDestPortIdx.description: The number of the port of the VCG entity that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

vcgXCDestIdx.name: vcgXCDestIdx
vcgXCDestIdx.description: The number of the VCG within the identified port that serves as the destination port for the cross connection.

vcgXCType.name: vcgXCType
vcgXCType.description: The type of cross connection between the identified source and destination VCG entities. This is a mandatory object when a row of the VCG cross connect table is created. Only 2-way and 2-way protected cross-connections are supported between VCGs.

vcgXCProtShelfNum.name: vcgXCProtShelfNum
vcgXCProtShelfNum.description: The number of the shelf of the VCG entity that serves as the protection port for the cross connection.

vcgXCProtSlotNum.name: vcgXCProtSlotNum
vcgXCProtSlotNum.description: The number of the slot of the VCG entity that serves as the protection port for the cross connection.

vcgXCProtPortNum.name: vcgXCProtPortNum
vcgXCProtPortNum.description: The number of the port of the VCG entity that serves as the protection port for the cross connection.

vcgXCProtNum.name: vcgXCProtNum
vcgXCProtNum.description: The number of the VCG within the identified port that serves as the protection port for the cross connection.

vcgXCRowStatus.name: vcgXCRowStatus
vcgXCRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the VCG cross connection table, which in turn controls the provisioning and de-provisioning of VCG cross connections.

stsnXCTable.name: stsnXCTable
stsnXCTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned cross connection between SONET STS-N facilities on Muxponder circuit packs.

stsnXCEntry.name: stsnXCEntry
stsnXCEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the STS-N cross connection table.

stsnXCStsnTypeIdx.name: stsnXCStsnTypeIdx
stsnXCStsnTypeIdx.description: The specific STS-N rate of the cross-connection.

stsnXCSrcShelfIdx.name: stsnXCSrcShelfIdx
stsnXCSrcShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the STS-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCSrcSlotIdx.name: stsnXCSrcSlotIdx
stsnXCSrcSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the STS-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCSrcPortIdx.name: stsnXCSrcPortIdx
stsnXCSrcPortIdx.description: The number of the port of the STS-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCSrcIdx.name: stsnXCSrcIdx
stsnXCSrcIdx.description: The number of the STS-N within the identified port that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCDestShelfIdx.name: stsnXCDestShelfIdx
stsnXCDestShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the STS-N facility that serves as the destination end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCDestSlotIdx.name: stsnXCDestSlotIdx
stsnXCDestSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the STS-N entity that serves as the destination end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCDestPortIdx.name: stsnXCDestPortIdx
stsnXCDestPortIdx.description: The number of the port of the STS-N entity that serves as the destination end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCDestIdx.name: stsnXCDestIdx
stsnXCDestIdx.description: The number of the STS-N within the identified port that serves as the destination end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCType.name: stsnXCType
stsnXCType.description: The type of cross connection between the identified source and destination STS-N facilities. This is a mandatory object when a row of the STS-N cross connect table is created. Only 2-way cross-connections are supported between STS-Ns.

stsnXCProtTypeNum.name: stsnXCProtTypeNum
stsnXCProtTypeNum.description: The rate of the STS-N facility that serves as the protection end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCProtShelfNum.name: stsnXCProtShelfNum
stsnXCProtShelfNum.description: The number of the shelf of the STS-N entity that serves as the protection end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCProtSlotNum.name: stsnXCProtSlotNum
stsnXCProtSlotNum.description: The number of the slot of the STS-N entity that serves as the protection end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCProtPortNum.name: stsnXCProtPortNum
stsnXCProtPortNum.description: The number of the port of the STS-N entity that serves as the protection end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCProtNum.name: stsnXCProtNum
stsnXCProtNum.description: The number of the STS-N within the identified port that serves as the protection end-point for the cross connection.

stsnXCRowStatus.name: stsnXCRowStatus
stsnXCRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the STS-N cross connection table, which in turn controls the provisioning and de-provisioning of STS-N cross connections.

vcnXCTable.name: vcnXCTable
vcnXCTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned cross connection between SDH VC-N facilities on Muxponder circuit packs.

vcnXCEntry.name: vcnXCEntry
vcnXCEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the VC-N cross connection table.

vcnXCVcnTypeIdx.name: vcnXCVcnTypeIdx
vcnXCVcnTypeIdx.description: The specific rate of the VC-N cross-connection.

vcnXCSrcShelfIdx.name: vcnXCSrcShelfIdx
vcnXCSrcShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf of the VC-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

vcnXCSrcSlotIdx.name: vcnXCSrcSlotIdx
vcnXCSrcSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot of the VC-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

vcnXCSrcPortIdx.name: vcnXCSrcPortIdx
vcnXCSrcPortIdx.description: The number of the port of the VC-N facility that serves as the source end-point for the cross connection.

DbBackupAndRestoreCmd.name: DbBackupAndRestoreCmd
DbBackupAndRestoreCmd.description: The MSCP maintains all provisionable data in non-volatile storage so that configuration settings are retained during system shutdowns and restarts. The configuration database is version controlled to facilitate the detection of an incompatible software load and/or database. The BTI 7000 Series supports user-initiated backup and restore operations of the configuration database through the SNMP Set requests performed on the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object with a value corresponding to the required action. In a backup operation, the database is uploaded to a user-specified network location (that is, a local PC or a remote PC) using the file transfer protocol (FTP), or it is stored locally on the MSCP. In a restore operation, the database is restored using a version of the file from an FTP server or locally from the MSCP. The integrity of the file is validated to ensure that it matches the current software load on the BTI 7000 Series. The DbBackupAndRestoreCmd textual convention is the value of the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object, which is used to activate a database backup operation, or the various steps of a database restore operation. These operations are initiated when a set request is performed on the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object with a value corresponding to the desired action, as explained below. A get request on this type returns the value noOp. The valid values for DbBackupAndRestoreCmd that can be used in a set operation are: - 'invokeBackup': used to perform a database backup operation. The operation may be used to perform a local database backup, or to save the database backup to a remote repository. - 'loadRestore': used to initiate a database restore operation. The operation may be the restoration of a local database backup or of a remote database backup - 'invokeRestore': continues a database restore operation after the loadRestore stage has completed. The database being restored is made active on the SCP circuit pack at this stage. - 'applyRestore': Obsolete this functionality is now done as part of the invokeRestore. - 'commitRestore': is used to complete a database restore operation and can be used after the applyRestore action completes - 'cancelRestore': is used to cancel and back out of a database restore operation in progress and can be used before the commitRestore action is called. In order for the set request on the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object to complete successfully, the values of other objects must be set in the same set request for some of the commands. The additional objects required to be set along with the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object for each DbBackupAndRestoreCmd value are listed below. - invokeBackup: must also set dbBackupAndRestoreType. If this object is set to remote, then the dbBackupAndRestoreAddress, dbBackupAndRestoreFtpUser and dbBackupAndRestorePswd object values must also be specified in the set request. The dbBackupAndRestoreCheckAlm object may optionally be set when the invokeBackup action is performed. Also when the dbBackupAndRestoreType is set to remote the dbBackupAndRestorePath is optional. If not specified the default name is used. - loadRestore: must also set dbBackupAndRestoreType. If this object is set to remote, then the dbBackupAndRestoreAddress, dbBackupAndRestorePath, dbBackupAndRestoreFtpUser and dbBackupAndRestorePswd object values must also be specified in the set request. The dbBackupAndRestoreCheckSysName object may be set when the loadRestore action is performed, but is not mandatory. - invokeRestore: must also set dbBackupAndRestoreInvokeFilename to confirm the name of the backed file to be used in the restore operation. Optionally, the dbBackupAndRestoreCheckAlm object may be set. - applyRestore, commitRestore, cancelRestore: no additional object values are required to be included for these set requests

DbBackupAndRestoreType.name: DbBackupAndRestoreType
DbBackupAndRestoreType.description: Indicates the type of database backup operation to be performed, or the type of database restore operation to be performed. The meaning of the values are as follows. - 'local': for a database backup, the backup is made on the NE itself; for a database restore, the restoration is from a local database backup file - 'remote': for a database backup, the backup is made to an external ftp server; for a database restore, the restoration is from a database file located on an external ftp server - 'remoteSftp': for a database backup, the backup is made to an external sftp server; for a database restore, the restoration is from a database file located on an external sftp server

dbBackupAndRestoreCmd.name: dbBackupAndRestoreCmd
dbBackupAndRestoreCmd.description: This object is used to activate the steps of a database backup or database restore operation. The description of the DbBackupAndRestoreCmd textual convention explains the usage of this object to perform these operations.

dbBackupAndRestoreType.name: dbBackupAndRestoreType
dbBackupAndRestoreType.description: This object is used to indicate whether a local database, or a remote database is involved in the backup or restore operation that is being activated with the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object, as explained in the DbBackupAndRestoreType textual convention.

dbBackupAndRestoreAddress.name: dbBackupAndRestoreAddress
dbBackupAndRestoreAddress.description: The IP address of an ftp server which the NE database is backed up to, or restored from. This object is used when the dbBackupAndRestoreType is set to remote.

dbBackupAndRestorePath.name: dbBackupAndRestorePath
dbBackupAndRestorePath.description: The directory path on the ftp server where where the NE database backup is to be saved to, or restored from. This object is used when the dbBackupAndRestoreType is set to remote.

dbBackupAndRestoreFtpUser.name: dbBackupAndRestoreFtpUser
dbBackupAndRestoreFtpUser.description: The user identifier to be used on the ftp server where the NE database backup is to be saved to, or restored from. This object is used when the dbBackupAndRestoreType is set to remote.

dbBackupAndRestoreFtpPswd.name: dbBackupAndRestoreFtpPswd
dbBackupAndRestoreFtpPswd.description: The password to be used on the ftp server where the NE database backup is to be saved to, or restored from. This object is used when the dbBackupAndRestoreType is set to remote.

dbBackupAndRestoreCheckAlm.name: dbBackupAndRestoreCheckAlm
dbBackupAndRestoreCheckAlm.description: This object is used to indicate whether or not the system is to be checked for active alarms before proceding with a backup or restore operation. If set to yes, the requested action will not be performed if alarms are active on the system. If not specified in the same set request as the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object, the value is defaulted to yes.

dbBackupAndRestoreCheckSysName.name: dbBackupAndRestoreCheckSysName
dbBackupAndRestoreCheckSysName.description: This object is used to indicate whether or not the system name of the NE targeted for a database restore operation against the system name embedded in the database backup file to be restored. If set to yes, the requested action will not be performed if system names do not match. If not specified in the same set request as the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object, the value is defaulted to yes.

dbBackupAndRestoreInvokeFilename.name: dbBackupAndRestoreInvokeFilename
dbBackupAndRestoreInvokeFilename.description: The name of the database backup file that is to be used in a database restore operation. This object is set along with the dbBackupAndRestoreCmd object when it is set to invokeRestore, as a confirmation that the database that is to be restored is the correct database. In order for the invokeRestore command to proceed, the value set for this object must match the value of the dbBackupAndRestoreFilename object.

dbBackupAndRestoreFilename.name: dbBackupAndRestoreFilename
dbBackupAndRestoreFilename.description: The name of the database backup file that is present and ready to be restored. The value of this field is valid after the completion of the loadRestore command.

dbBackupAndRestoreResult.name: dbBackupAndRestoreResult
dbBackupAndRestoreResult.description: Indicates if the identified stage of the database backup and restore process has resulted in success or failure.

SwUpgradeCmd.name: SwUpgradeCmd
SwUpgradeCmd.description: All BTI 7000 Series circuit packs are shipped with pre-loaded software. At system commissioning, it is not necessary to start the system by loading software. However, during the life cycle of the BTI 7000 Series, it might be necessary to upgrade the system software. Normally, the system software is upgraded to: � Support the functionality of new circuit packs � Provide new features for existing circuit packs � Add specific software improvements Performing a system software upgrade on the BTI 7000 Series is non-service affecting. The upgrade process is designed for application environments that require that the optical signals passing through the BTI 7000 Series are not interrupted. The BTI 7000 Series supports a user-initiated software upgrade operation through the SNMP Set requests performed on the swUpgradeCmd object with a value corresponding to the required action. The SwUpgradeCmd textual convention is the value of the swUpgradeCmd object, which is used to activate the various steps of the software upgrade procedure on the system. These steps are initiated when a set request is performed on the swUpgradeCmd object with a value corresponding to the desired action, as explained below. A get request will return the value noOp. The valid values for SwUpgradeCmd that can be used in a set operation are: - 'checkUpgrade': used to perform a pre-upgrade check of the system to ensure that it is ready for the upgrade process, and that the load files on the server are accessible. - 'loadUpgrade': used to initiate a system upgrade by downloading the load files from a remote server to the SCP software load storage area. - 'invokeUpgrade': continues a system upgrade operation after the loadUpgrade stage has completed. First the upgrade load is installed on all circuit packs in the system, then each card is rebooted to run the upgrade load. - 'commitUpgrade': is used to complete a system upgrade operation and can be used after the invkUpgrade action completes - 'cancelUpgrade': is used to cancel and back out of a system software upgrade operation in progress and can be used before the cmmtUpgrade action is called. - 'invokeScpUpgrade': is a special-purpose upgrade step used in place of the invkUpgrade value when an upgrade is being performed on an SCP pack only. Such a targeted upgrade is valid only when an SCP pack is replaced and the new pack requires a software upgrade to make its software version consistent with the system In order for the set request on the swUpgradeCmd object to complete successfully, the values of other objects must be set in the same set request for some of the commands. The additional objects required to be set along with the swUpgradeCmd object for each SwUpgradeCmd value are listed below. - checkUpgrade, loadUpgrade: must also set swUpgradeAddress, swUpgradePath, swUpgradeFtpUser, swUpgradeFtpPswd and swUpgradeFileTransferType object values to indicate where the ftp or sftp server with the upgrade load files is to be found, along with access parameters. - invokeUpgrade, invokeScpUpgrade: must also set the swUpgradeInvokeRelNum object to confirm the software version that is to be used in the upgrade. The swUpgradeCheckAlm object may be set, but is not mandatory. - commitUpgrade, cancelUpgrade: no additional object values are required to be specified for these set requests.

SwUpgradeFileTransferType.name: SwUpgradeFileTransferType
SwUpgradeFileTransferType.description: Indicates the protocol of the file transfer. - 'ftp': an external ftp server is the source for the load to be transfered. - 'sftp': an external sftp server is the source for the load to be transfered.

swUpgradeCmd.name: swUpgradeCmd
swUpgradeCmd.description: This object is used to activate the steps of a software upgrade procedure on the system. The description of the SwUpgradeCmd textual convention explains the usage of this object to perform these operations.

swUpgradeAddress.name: swUpgradeAddress
swUpgradeAddress.description: The IP address of an ftp or sftp server from which the software load files for the upgrade are to be downloaded.

swUpgradePath.name: swUpgradePath
swUpgradePath.description: The directory path on the upgrade load files ftp or sftp server where the software load files are found.

swUpgradeFtpUser.name: swUpgradeFtpUser
swUpgradeFtpUser.description: The user identifier to be used on the ftp or sftp server from which the upgrade load is downloaded.

swUpgradeFtpPswd.name: swUpgradeFtpPswd
swUpgradeFtpPswd.description: The password to be used on the ftp or sftp server from which the upgrade load is downloaded.

swUpgradeInvokeRelNum.name: swUpgradeInvokeRelNum
swUpgradeInvokeRelNum.description: The release number of the software upgrade load that is targeted in a software upgrade invoke operation. This object must be set along with the swUpgradeCmd object when it is set to invokeUpgrade or invokeScpUpgrade, as a confirmation that the software load to be used in the upgrade is the correct load.

swUpgradeCheckAlm.name: swUpgradeCheckAlm
swUpgradeCheckAlm.description: This object is used to indicate whether or not the system is to be checked for active alarms before proceding with a software upgrade operation. If set to yes, the requested action will not be performed if alarms are active on the system. If not specified in the same set request as the swUpgradeCmd object, the value is defaulted to yes.

swUpgradeActiveRelNum.name: swUpgradeActiveRelNum
swUpgradeActiveRelNum.description: The release number of the software load that is installed on the system and is currently active.

swUpgradeInactiveRelNum.name: swUpgradeInactiveRelNum
swUpgradeInactiveRelNum.description: The release number of the software load that is installed on the system and is currently inactive.

swUpgradeFileTransferType.name: swUpgradeFileTransferType
swUpgradeFileTransferType.description: This object is used to define the file transfer protocol used to retreive the load from a remote server. The default value is ftp

cpRestartOpShelfIdx.name: cpRestartOpShelfIdx
cpRestartOpShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the circuit pack targeted for the restart operation is provisioned.

cpRestartOpSlotIdx.name: cpRestartOpSlotIdx
cpRestartOpSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot in which the circuit pack targeted for the restart operation is provisioned. For ESI type circuit packs, the slot will be 0. For CCM type circuit packs, the slot can only be 1 or 2.

cpRestartOpCmd.name: cpRestartOpCmd
cpRestartOpCmd.description: Used to perform a circuit pack restart operation as follows. - warmRestart causes a restart of the main processor only; traffic is not affected - coldRestart causes a full circuit pack restart, including data path - powerOn causes a circuit pack that has been powered down due to a high temperature or voltage event to power on. When this object is read, the value noOp is returned.

oaOOBRSDOpShelfIdx.name: oaOOBRSDOpShelfIdx

oaOOBRSDOpSlotIdx.name: oaOOBRSDOpSlotIdx
oaOOBRSDOpSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot within which the optical amplifier facility targeted for the operation is provisioned.

oaOOBRSDOpIdx.name: oaOOBRSDOpIdx

oaOOBRSDOpCmd.name: oaOOBRSDOpCmd
oaOOBRSDOpCmd.description: Used to perform a Override Optical Back Reflection Shutdown operation when this object is set to overrideOBRSD. When read, this object returns noOp.

oaOOBRSDOpTimer.name: oaOOBRSDOpTimer
oaOOBRSDOpTimer.description: Used to specify the time duration of an override back reflection shutdown operation. It is only valid to set the value of this object in the same set request as for the oaOOBRSDOpCmd object. Despite the indicated value range, the actual supported range is 20 to 600. The value 0 is returned when this object is read, even if an overrideOBRSD operation is in progress.

DataCommsPingCmd.name: DataCommsPingCmd
DataCommsPingCmd.description: The DataCommsPingCmd textual convention is the value of the dataCommsPingCmd object which is used to perform a ping operation over the NE's OSC. The operation is initiated when a set request is performed on the dataCommsPingCmd object with a value corresponding to the ping action, as explained below. The valid values for DataCommsPingCmd that can be used in a set operation are: - 'ping', used to trigger the ping operation over the OSC A value of 'pingInProgress' is returned when the dataCommsPingCmd object is read in a get operation if the ping command entered has not yet completed, otherwise 'noOp' is returned. In order for the set request on a DataCommsPingCmd object to complete successfully, the dataCommsPingCmd object, along with the dataCommdPingAddress and optionally the dataCommsPingNumAttemps objects must be set in the same set request for a given row of the table. The purpose of these objects is: - dataCommsPingAddress: indicates the IP Address which is the target of the ping operation - dataCommsPingNumAttempts: indicates how many ping attempts are to be made in the ping operation Once the dataCommsPingCmd operation is completed by way of the set operation on the dataCommsPingCmd and associated objects, the result of the operation is checked by performing a get operation on the dataCommsPingNumSuccesses object. When the ping operation completes, the value of this object will be set to the number of the attempted ping trials that resulted in a successful ping.

dataCommsPingTable.name: dataCommsPingTable
dataCommsPingTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned circuit pack on the NE from which an IP ping request can be sent. This includes all SCP and OSC type packs.

dataCommsPingEntry.name: dataCommsPingEntry
dataCommsPingEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the data comms ping table.

dataCommsPingCpTypeIdx.name: dataCommsPingCpTypeIdx
dataCommsPingCpTypeIdx.description: This object is used to indicate the type of circuit pack from which the ping operation is to be conducted using the dataCommsPingCmd object.

dataCommsPingShelfIdx.name: dataCommsPingShelfIdx
dataCommsPingShelfIdx.description: This object is used to indicate the shelf number containing the circuit pack from which the ping operation is to be conducted using the dataCommsPingCmd object.

dataCommsPingSlotIdx.name: dataCommsPingSlotIdx
dataCommsPingSlotIdx.description: This object is used to indicate the slot number containing the circuit pack from which the ping operation is to be conducted using the dataCommsPingCmd object.

dataCommsPingCmd.name: dataCommsPingCmd
dataCommsPingCmd.description: This object is used to trigger a ping operation from an OSC or SCP circuit pack. The description of DataCommsPingCmd textual convention explains the usage of this object to perform the ping operation.

dataCommsPingAddress.name: dataCommsPingAddress
dataCommsPingAddress.description: This object is used to indicate the IP Address which is the target of the ping operation to be conducted using the dataCommsPingCmd object.

dataCommsPingNumAttempts.name: dataCommsPingNumAttempts
dataCommsPingNumAttempts.description: This object is used to indicate how many ping attempts are to be made in the ping operation to be conducted using the dataCommsPingCmd object. The default is 3.

dataCommsPingNumSuccesses.name: dataCommsPingNumSuccesses
dataCommsPingNumSuccesses.description: This object is used to indicate how many ping trials attempted in the ping operation resulted in a successful ping completion.
