cpSynchronizationShelfIdx.name: cpSynchronizationShelfIdx
cpSynchronizationShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the circuit pack is provisioned.

cpSynchronizationSlotIdx.name: cpSynchronizationSlotIdx
cpSynchronizationSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot in which the circuit pack is provisioned.

cpSynchronizationTimingMode.name: cpSynchronizationTimingMode
cpSynchronizationTimingMode.description: The timing mode used for SONET synchronization on the pack.

cpSynchronizationPrimRefSrcPortNum.name: cpSynchronizationPrimRefSrcPortNum
cpSynchronizationPrimRefSrcPortNum.description: The port number of the SONET facility that serves as the primary timing reference source. When the value is 0, the primary reference is not configured.

cpSynchronizationPrimRefProtStatus.name: cpSynchronizationPrimRefProtStatus
cpSynchronizationPrimRefProtStatus.description: The protection status of the primary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationPrimProtStatQlfr.name: cpSynchronizationPrimProtStatQlfr
cpSynchronizationPrimProtStatQlfr.description: A textual list of qualifiers of the reported protection status of the primary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationSecRefSrcPortNum.name: cpSynchronizationSecRefSrcPortNum
cpSynchronizationSecRefSrcPortNum.description: The port number of the SONET facility that serves as the secondary timing reference source. When the value is 0, the secondary reference is not configured.

cpSynchronizationSecRefProtStatus.name: cpSynchronizationSecRefProtStatus
cpSynchronizationSecRefProtStatus.description: The protection status of the secondary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationSecProtStatQlfr.name: cpSynchronizationSecProtStatQlfr
cpSynchronizationSecProtStatQlfr.description: A textual list of qualifiers of the reported protection status of the secondary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationPrimRefBasicSSM.name: cpSynchronizationPrimRefBasicSSM
cpSynchronizationPrimRefBasicSSM.description: Used to enable basic Synchronization Status Messaging (SSM) functionality on the primary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationSecRefBasicSSM.name: cpSynchronizationSecRefBasicSSM
cpSynchronizationSecRefBasicSSM.description: Used to enable basic Synchronization Status Messaging (SSM) functionality on the primary timing reference source.

cpSynchronizationSwEvtType.name: cpSynchronizationSwEvtType
cpSynchronizationSwEvtType.description: Indicates the type of timing reference switching event that has occurred on the circuit pack.

networkNeighborTable.name: networkNeighborTable
networkNeighborTable.description: This table is used to store information on the network neighbors of the local network element. Each row contains information on a specific network neighbor.

networkNeighborEntry.name: networkNeighborEntry
networkNeighborEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the network neighbor table.

networkNeighborIdx.name: networkNeighborIdx
networkNeighborIdx.description: A textual identifier of the network neighbor.

networkNeighborIPAddr.name: networkNeighborIPAddr
networkNeighborIPAddr.description: The primary IP Address of the network neighbor.

networkNeighborRowStatus.name: networkNeighborRowStatus
networkNeighborRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the network neighbor table.

ospfGeneralTable.name: ospfGeneralTable
ospfGeneralTable.description: This table contains all of general OSPF parameters for the network element. The group can be created and deleted but only one entry can exist in the table.

ospfGeneralGroupEntry.name: ospfGeneralGroupEntry
ospfGeneralGroupEntry.description: The list entry for the OSPF General Group parameters.

ospfIdx.name: ospfIdx
ospfIdx.description: An index used to identify the OSPF instance in order to alow for creation and deletion to allow compatibility with TL1 and CLI interfaces. Note the value is always 1.

ospfRouterId.name: ospfRouterId
ospfRouterId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the router. By convention, to ensure uniqueness, this should default to the value of one of the router's IP interface addresses. This object is persistent.

ospfAdminStat.name: ospfAdminStat
ospfAdminStat.description: The administrative status of OSPF in the router. The value 'enabled' denotes that the OSPF Process is active on at least one interface; 'disabled' disables it on all interfaces. This object is persistent.

ospfVersionNumber.name: ospfVersionNumber
ospfVersionNumber.description: The current version number of the OSPF protocol is 2.

ospfAreaBdrRtrStatus.name: ospfAreaBdrRtrStatus
ospfAreaBdrRtrStatus.description: A flag to note whether this router is an Area Border Router.

ospfRouteRedist.name: ospfRouteRedist
ospfRouteRedist.description: Indicates the extent of route redistribution. Static - static routes, Connected - routes connected to the node. DefOrig - default routes from adjacent nodes.

ospfAreaId.name: ospfAreaId
ospfAreaId.description: The area ID associated with this OSPF item. Note that although the area ID has the format of an IP Address it is not actually an IP address.

ospfRowStatus.name: ospfRowStatus
ospfRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of the ospf General Group parameters.

ospfIfTable.name: ospfIfTable
ospfIfTable.description: The OSPF Interface Table describes the interfaces from the viewpoint of OSPF.

ospfIfEntry.name: ospfIfEntry
ospfIfEntry.description: The OSPF interface entry describes one interface from the viewpoint of OSPF. Information in this table is persistent and when this object is written the entity is saved to non-volatile storage.

ospfIfSwitchId.name: ospfIfSwitchId
ospfIfSwitchId.description: The number of the switch id on which the OSPF interface exists. Set to zero if the switchId a switch Id is not applicable for identification of the OSPF interface.

ospfIfShelfIdx.name: ospfIfShelfIdx
ospfIfShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf on which the OSPF interface exists.

ospfIfSlotIdx.name: ospfIfSlotIdx
ospfIfSlotIdx.description: The number of the slot within the shelf corresponding to the OSPF interface.

ospfIfType.name: ospfIfType
ospfIfType.description: The type of the interface corresponding to the OSPF interface. Set to zero if the ospfIfType is not applicable for identification of the OSPF interface.

ospfIfIdx.name: ospfIfIdx
ospfIfIdx.description: The number of the interface within the slot corresponding to the OSPF interface.

ospfIfSubIdx.name: ospfIfSubIdx
ospfIfSubIdx.description: The number of the sub-interface that the OSFP Interface corresponds to. Set to zero if the ospfIfSubIdx is not applicable for identification of the OSPF interface.

ospfIfAreaId.name: ospfIfAreaId
ospfIfAreaId.description: A 32-bit integer uniquely identifying the area to which the interface connects. Area ID 0.0.0.0 is used for the OSPF backbone.

ospfIfAdminStat.name: ospfIfAdminStat
ospfIfAdminStat.description: The OSPF interface's administrative status. The value formed on the interface, and the interface will be advertised as an internal route to some area. The value 'disabled' denotes that the interface is external to OSPF.

ospfIfRtrPriority.name: ospfIfRtrPriority
ospfIfRtrPriority.description: The priority of this interface. Used in multi-access networks, this field is used in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the router is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network. In the event of a tie in this value, routers will use their Router ID as a tie breaker.

ospfIfTransitDelay.name: ospfIfTransitDelay
ospfIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a link state update packet over this interface. Note that the minimal value SHOULD be 1 second.

ospfIfRetransInterval.name: ospfIfRetransInterval
ospfIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state advertisement retransmissions, for adjacencies belonging to this interface. This value is also used when retransmitting database description and Link State request packets. Note that minimal value SHOULD be 1 second.

ospfIfHelloInterval.name: ospfIfHelloInterval
ospfIfHelloInterval.description: The length of time, in seconds, between the Hello packets that the router sends on the interface. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.name: ospfIfRtrDeadInterval
ospfIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down. This should be some multiple of the Hello interval. This value must be the same for all routers attached to a common network.

ospfIfMetricValue.name: ospfIfMetricValue
ospfIfMetricValue.description: A metric used to identify the 'cost' associated with using this interface.

ospfIfStatus.name: ospfIfStatus
ospfIfStatus.description: This object permits management of the table by facilitating actions such as row creation, construction, and destruction. The value of this object has no effect on whether other objects in this conceptual row can be modified.

ospfLsdbTable.name: ospfLsdbTable
ospfLsdbTable.description: The OSPF Process's link state database (LSDB). The LSDB contains the link state advertisements from throughout the areas that the device is attached to.

ospfLsdbAreaId.name: ospfLsdbAreaId
ospfLsdbAreaId.description: The 32-bit identifier of the area from which the LSA was received.

ospfLsdbType.name: ospfLsdbType
ospfLsdbType.description: The type of the link state advertisement. Each link state type has a separate advertisement format

ospfLsdbLsid.name: ospfLsdbLsid
ospfLsdbLsid.description: The Link State ID is an LS Type Specific field containing either a Router ID or an IP address; it identifies the piece of the routing domain that is being described by the advertisement.

ospfLsdbRouterId.name: ospfLsdbRouterId
ospfLsdbRouterId.description: The 32-bit number that uniquely identifies the originating router in the Autonomous System.

ospfLsdbSequence.name: ospfLsdbSequence
ospfLsdbSequence.description: The sequence number field is a signed 32-bit integer. It starts with the value '80000001'h, or -'7FFFFFFF'h, and increments until '7FFFFFFF'h. Thus, a typical sequence number will be very negative. It is used to detect old and duplicate Link State Advertisements. The space of sequence numbers is linearly ordered. The larger the sequence number, the more recent the advertisement.

ospfLsdbAge.name: ospfLsdbAge
ospfLsdbAge.description: This field is the age of the link state advertisement in seconds.

ospfLsdbChecksum.name: ospfLsdbChecksum
ospfLsdbChecksum.description: This field is the checksum of the complete contents of the advertisement, excepting the age field. The age field is excepted so that an advertisement's age can be incremented without updating the checksum. The checksum used is the same that is used for ISO connectionless datagrams; it is commonly referred to as the Fletcher checksum.

ospfNbrTable.name: ospfNbrTable
ospfNbrTable.description: A table describing all non-virtual neighbors in the locality of the OSPF router.

ospfNbrEntry.name: ospfNbrEntry
ospfNbrEntry.description: The information regarding a single neighbor. Information in this table is persistent and when this object is written the entity SHOULD save the change to non-volatile storage.

ospfNbrIpAddr.name: ospfNbrIpAddr
ospfNbrIpAddr.description: The IP address this neighbor is using in its IP source address. Note that, on addressless links, this will not be 0.0.0.0 but the address of another of the neighbor's interfaces.

ospfNbrAddressLessIndex.name: ospfNbrAddressLessIndex
ospfNbrAddressLessIndex.description: On an interface having an IP address, zero. On addressless interfaces, the corresponding value of ifIndex in the Internet Standard MIB. On row creation, this can be derived from the instance.

ospfNbrRtrId.name: ospfNbrRtrId
ospfNbrRtrId.description: A 32-bit integer (represented as a type IpAddress) uniquely identifying the neighboring router in the Autonomous System.

ospfNbrOptions.name: ospfNbrOptions
ospfNbrOptions.description: A bit mask corresponding to the neighbor's options field. Bit 0, if set, indicates that the system will operate on Type of Service metrics other than TOS 0. If zero, the neighbor will ignore all metrics except the TOS 0 metric. Bit 1, if set, indicates that the associated area accepts and operates on external information; if zero, it is a stub area. Bit 2, if set, indicates that the system is capable of routing IP multicast datagrams, that is that it implements the multicast extensions to OSPF. Bit 3, if set, indicates that the associated area is an NSSA. These areas are capable of carrying type-7 external advertisements, which are translated into type-5 external advertisements at NSSA borders.

ospfNbrPriority.name: ospfNbrPriority
ospfNbrPriority.description: The priority of this neighbor in the designated router election algorithm. The value 0 signifies that the neighbor is not eligible to become the designated router on this particular network.

ospfNbrState.name: ospfNbrState
ospfNbrState.description: The state of the relationship with this neighbor.

pvxL2IntfTable.name: pvxL2IntfTable
pvxL2IntfTable.description: This table contains one row for every provisioned Ethernet facility on the system. Each row contains a list of attributes that pertain to the facility.

pvxL2IntfEntry.name: pvxL2IntfEntry
pvxL2IntfEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the ethIntfTable table.

pvxL2IntfSwitchIdx.name: pvxL2IntfSwitchIdx
pvxL2IntfSwitchIdx.description: The number of the switch id of the provisioned ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfShelfIdx.name: pvxL2IntfShelfIdx
pvxL2IntfShelfIdx.description: The number of the shelf id of the provisioned ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfSlotIdx.name: pvxL2IntfSlotIdx
pvxL2IntfSlotIdx.description: The number of the instance id of the provisioned ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfPortTypeIdx.name: pvxL2IntfPortTypeIdx
pvxL2IntfPortTypeIdx.description: The number of the instance id of the provisioned ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfPortIdx.name: pvxL2IntfPortIdx
pvxL2IntfPortIdx.description: The number of the port on the circuit pack on which the ethernet facility is provisioned.

pvxL2IntfAdminStatus.name: pvxL2IntfAdminStatus
pvxL2IntfAdminStatus.description: The administrative status of the Ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfOperStatus.name: pvxL2IntfOperStatus
pvxL2IntfOperStatus.description: The reported operational status of the Ethernet facility.

pvxL2IntfType.name: pvxL2IntfType
pvxL2IntfType.description: This object is used to configure the type of a interface.

pvxL2IntfSTpid.name: pvxL2IntfSTpid
pvxL2IntfSTpid.description: The Ethernet type (TPID) of the S-TAG

pvxL2IntfPvid.name: pvxL2IntfPvid
pvxL2IntfPvid.description: The PVID (port-based VLAN ID) for the port

pvxL2IntfDefaultPriority.name: pvxL2IntfDefaultPriority
pvxL2IntfDefaultPriority.description: This object sets the default priority of the interface.

pvxL2IntfAllowedFrames.name: pvxL2IntfAllowedFrames
pvxL2IntfAllowedFrames.description: TODO: Does this feild need to support OR of the options?

pvxL2IntfIngressFiltering.name: pvxL2IntfIngressFiltering
pvxL2IntfIngressFiltering.description: When this is true(1) the device will discard incoming frames for VLANs which do not include this Port in its Member set. When false(2), the port will accept all incoming frames. This control does not affect VLAN independent BPDU frames, such as GVRP and STP. It does affect VLAN dependent BPDU frames, such as GMRP.

pvxL2IntfMACAddr.name: pvxL2IntfMACAddr
pvxL2IntfMACAddr.description: The MAC address of the interface.

pvxL2IntfRateLimit.name: pvxL2IntfRateLimit
pvxL2IntfRateLimit.description: This represents the interface rate limit in kilobits/s.

pvxL2IntfCoSProfileId.name: pvxL2IntfCoSProfileId
pvxL2IntfCoSProfileId.description: This represents the Class of service profile for the interface.

pvxL2IntfIsUNI.name: pvxL2IntfIsUNI
pvxL2IntfIsUNI.description: The Switch port type. The default value set by the switch is neither.

pvxL2IntfSchedProfName.name: pvxL2IntfSchedProfName
pvxL2IntfSchedProfName.description: The scheduler profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfPriTCMapProfName.name: pvxL2IntfPriTCMapProfName
pvxL2IntfPriTCMapProfName.description: The priority to traffic class map profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfPCPCodingProfName.name: pvxL2IntfPCPCodingProfName
pvxL2IntfPCPCodingProfName.description: The scheduler profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfDscpPHBProfName.name: pvxL2IntfDscpPHBProfName
pvxL2IntfDscpPHBProfName.description: The internal priority setting for DSCP profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfCtrlFrmProfileName.name: pvxL2IntfCtrlFrmProfileName
pvxL2IntfCtrlFrmProfileName.description: The L2 control frame profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfUseDei.name: pvxL2IntfUseDei
pvxL2IntfUseDei.description: Used by PNP port. By default, it is set to false by the switch.

pvxL2IntfIngressBandwidthProfile.name: pvxL2IntfIngressBandwidthProfile
pvxL2IntfIngressBandwidthProfile.description: The ingress policy map profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfEgressBandwidthProfile.name: pvxL2IntfEgressBandwidthProfile
pvxL2IntfEgressBandwidthProfile.description: The egress policy map profile used by the interface.

pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingPCP.name: pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingPCP
pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingPCP.description: Used by all port type. By default, it is set to true by the switch.

pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingDscp.name: pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingDscp
pvxL2IntfTrustIncomingDscp.description: Used by all port type. By default, it is set to true by the switch.

pvxL2IntfBcastLimit.name: pvxL2IntfBcastLimit
pvxL2IntfBcastLimit.description: Broadcast rate limit as percentage of the line rate for the port with default value of 100 (no storm control).

pvxL2IntfMcastLimit.name: pvxL2IntfMcastLimit
pvxL2IntfMcastLimit.description: Multicast rate limit as percentage of the line rate for the port with default value of 100 (no storm control).

pvxL2IntfDlfLimit.name: pvxL2IntfDlfLimit
pvxL2IntfDlfLimit.description: Unicast DLF rate limit as percentage of the line rate for the port with default value of 100 (no storm control).

pvxL2IntfRowStatus.name: pvxL2IntfRowStatus
pvxL2IntfRowStatus.description: Used to control the addition and deletion of entries in the PVX L2 Interface table.

setErrorCode.name: setErrorCode
setErrorCode.description: The BTI-specific error code for the set request failure.

setErrorDesc.name: setErrorDesc
setErrorDesc.description: A textual description string that explains the reason for the failed set request.

trapSeqNum.name: trapSeqNum
trapSeqNum.description: A integer value indicating the place of the trap notification message within the continual sequence of all notification messages issued by the system.

evtDateAndTime.name: evtDateAndTime
evtDateAndTime.description: The date and time at which an event notification was issued by the system.

tcaIntervalType.name: tcaIntervalType
tcaIntervalType.description: The type of PM bin according to interval length during which a performance monitoring threshold crossing occurred.

tcaDateAndTime.name: tcaDateAndTime
tcaDateAndTime.description: The date and time of the performance monitoring interval for which a performance monitoring threshold crossing alert is generated.

tcaMontype.name: tcaMontype
tcaMontype.description: Identify the performance monitoring monitored type for which a threshold crossing alert is generated.

tcaValue.name: tcaValue
tcaValue.description: The measured value of the monitored type for which a performance monitoring threshold crossing alert is generated.

tcaThreshold.name: tcaThreshold
tcaThreshold.description: The threshold for the monitored type that was exceeded resulting in the generation of a performance monnitoring threshold crossing alert.

evtDescription.name: evtDescription
evtDescription.description: A textual decription of the event.

evtObjectType.name: evtObjectType
evtObjectType.description: Identifies the type of managed object against which the event notification is raised.

evtCodeType.name: evtCodeType
evtCodeType.description: This object value uniquely identifies the type of event that has been generated.

dbChangeDateAndTime.name: dbChangeDateAndTime
dbChangeDateAndTime.description: The date and time at which a database change notification was issued by the system.

dbChangeSeqNum.name: dbChangeSeqNum
dbChangeSeqNum.description: A integer value indicating the place of a database change notification message within the continual sequence of all database messages issued by the system.

dbChangeOID.name: dbChangeOID
dbChangeOID.description: The OID of the object instance whose value has been changed in the database.

condNotifCtrlTable.name: condNotifCtrlTable
condNotifCtrlTable.description: This table contains one row for every condition notification associated with a raise.

condNotifCtrlEntry.name: condNotifCtrlEntry
condNotifCtrlEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the condition notification control table.

condNotifObjId.name: condNotifObjId
condNotifObjId.description: The specific condition notification to set the severity for. The value must correspond to the raise condition not the clear.

condNotifSeverity.name: condNotifSeverity
condNotifSeverity.description: The severity associated with the condition notification. - Only certain values are permitted for the set: default, critial, major, minor, notAlarmed. - Only certain values are visible for the get: critial, major, minor, major-minor, notAlarmed

condNotifDefaultSeverity.name: condNotifDefaultSeverity
condNotifDefaultSeverity.description: The default severity associated with the condition notification. Only certain of the CondSeverity values are visible: critial, major, minor, major-minor, notAlarmed

envCondAttrTable.name: envCondAttrTable
envCondAttrTable.description: This table is used to manage the configuration of environmental alarm inputs. It contains one row for each environmental condition input on the NE.

envCondAttrEntry.name: envCondAttrEntry
envCondAttrEntry.description: The conceptual row object of the environmental condition attribute table.

envCondAttrHKIIdx.name: envCondAttrHKIIdx
envCondAttrHKIIdx.description: The number of the housekeeping input which drives the activation of the environmental condition configured by this entry of the table.

envCondAttrSeverity.name: envCondAttrSeverity
envCondAttrSeverity.description: The severity reported for the configured environmental condition when it is raised. The valid values are: - minor - major - critical - notAlarmed

envCondAttrCodeType.name: envCondAttrCodeType
envCondAttrCodeType.description: The code for the specific environmental condition that is reported when the housekeeping input indicates that the condition is active.

envCondAttrDescription.name: envCondAttrDescription
envCondAttrDescription.description: The textual decription of the environmental condition that is reported when the condition is raised.

envCondAttrInputType.name: envCondAttrInputType
envCondAttrInputType.description: Specifies how the housekeeping input which drives the reporting of the environmental condition is interpreted.

eventNotifState.name: eventNotifState
eventNotifState.description: Allows all events to be either disabled or enabled.

shelfInvPluginEvt.name: shelfInvPluginEvt
shelfInvPluginEvt.description: A shelf has been detected through the shelf interconnect.

shelfInvUnpluginEvt.name: shelfInvUnpluginEvt
shelfInvUnpluginEvt.description: A previously detected shelf is no longer detected through the shelf interconnect.

slotInvPluginEvt.name: slotInvPluginEvt
slotInvPluginEvt.description: A circuit pack has been inserted into the identified slot.

slotInvUnpluginEvt.name: slotInvUnpluginEvt
slotInvUnpluginEvt.description: A circuit pack has been removed from the identified slot.

slotInvUpgradeStageResultEvt.name: slotInvUpgradeStageResultEvt
slotInvUpgradeStageResultEvt.description: The software upgrade process on the circuit pack in the identified slot has completed a stage.

pluggableInvPluginEvt.name: pluggableInvPluginEvt
pluggableInvPluginEvt.description: A pluggable transceiver has been inserted into the identified port.

pluggableInvUnpluginEvt.name: pluggableInvUnpluginEvt
pluggableInvUnpluginEvt.description: A pluggable transceiver has been removed from the identified port.

shelfStatusChangeEvt.name: shelfStatusChangeEvt
shelfStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the shelf's operational status or operational status qualifier.

cpStatusChangeEvt.name: cpStatusChangeEvt
cpStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the circuit pack's operational status or operational status qualifier.

cpCheckUpgradeResultEvt.name: cpCheckUpgradeResultEvt
cpCheckUpgradeResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of the check upgrade step of the system-wide software upgrade process.

cpUpgradeTransferResultEvt.name: cpUpgradeTransferResultEvt
cpUpgradeTransferResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of the software download step of the system-wide software upgrade process.

cpUpgradeStageResultEvt.name: cpUpgradeStageResultEvt
cpUpgradeStageResultEvt.description: The software upgrade process on the active circuit pack in the identified slot has completed a stage.

cpDbBackupResultEvt.name: cpDbBackupResultEvt
cpDbBackupResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of an NE database backup operation.

cpDbRestoreTransferResultEvt.name: cpDbRestoreTransferResultEvt
cpDbRestoreTransferResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of the database download step of the NE database restore process.

cpDbInvokeResultEvt.name: cpDbInvokeResultEvt
cpDbInvokeResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of the invoke step of the NE database restore process.

cpDbApplyResultEvt.name: cpDbApplyResultEvt
cpDbApplyResultEvt.description: Indicates the result of the accept step of the NE database restore process.

oaStatusChangeEvt.name: oaStatusChangeEvt
oaStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the optical amplifier's operational status or operational status qualifier.

xcvrStatusChangeEvt.name: xcvrStatusChangeEvt
xcvrStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the transceiver's operational status or operational status qualifier.

xcvrProtSwitchEvt.name: xcvrProtSwitchEvt
xcvrProtSwitchEvt.description: A protection switch has occured on the optical transceiver facility.

xcvrTcaEvt.name: xcvrTcaEvt
xcvrTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on an optical transceiver port.

amdStatusChangeEvt.name: amdStatusChangeEvt
amdStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of an active multiplexer-demultiplexer port.

oscStatusChangeEvt.name: oscStatusChangeEvt
oscStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the optical supervisory channels's operational status or operational status qualifier.

netMgmtStatusChangeEvt.name: netMgmtStatusChangeEvt
netMgmtStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the network management interface's operational status or operational status qualifier.

ocnStatusChangeEvt.name: ocnStatusChangeEvt
ocnStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a SONET OC-N facility port.

ocnTcaEvt.name: ocnTcaEvt
ocnTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a SONET OC-N facility.

ocnProtSwitchEvt.name: ocnProtSwitchEvt
ocnProtSwitchEvt.description: A protection switch has occured on the identified OC-N facility.

stsnProtSwitchEvt.name: stsnProtSwitchEvt
stsnProtSwitchEvt.description: A protection switch has occured on the identified STS-N channel.

stsnTcaEvt.name: stsnTcaEvt
stsnTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a SONET STS-N facility.

stmnStatusChangeEvt.name: stmnStatusChangeEvt
stmnStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a SDH STM-N facility port.

stmnTcaEvt.name: stmnTcaEvt
stmnTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a SDH STM-N facility.

stmnProtSwitchEvt.name: stmnProtSwitchEvt
stmnProtSwitchEvt.description: A protection switch has occured on the identified STM-N facility.

vcnProtSwitchEvt.name: vcnProtSwitchEvt
vcnProtSwitchEvt.description: A protection switch has occured on the identified VC-N channel.

vcnTcaEvt.name: vcnTcaEvt
vcnTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a SDH VC-N facility.

geStatusChangeEvt.name: geStatusChangeEvt
geStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a Gigabit Ethernet facility port.

geTcaEvt.name: geTcaEvt
geTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a Gigabit Ethernet facility.

fcStatusChangeEvt.name: fcStatusChangeEvt
fcStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a Fiber Channel facility port.

fcTcaEvt.name: fcTcaEvt
fcTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a Fiber Channel facility.

ethL1IFStatusChangeEvt.name: ethL1IFStatusChangeEvt
ethL1IFStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a L1 Ethernet facility port.

ethL1IFTcaEvt.name: ethL1IFTcaEvt
ethL1IFTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on an Ethernet Layer 1 interface facility.

pvxL2IFTcaEvt.name: pvxL2IFTcaEvt
pvxL2IFTcaEvt.description: This trap provides a threshold crossing alert for a performance monitoring statistic on a PVX Pack Ethernet Layer 2 interface facility.

briStatusChangeEvt.name: briStatusChangeEvt
briStatusChangeEvt.description: Notification of a change in the operational status or operational status qualifier of a BRI facility port.

cpSynchronizationSwitchEvt.name: cpSynchronizationSwitchEvt
cpSynchronizationSwitchEvt.description: A synchronization timing reference switch has occurred on the identified circuit pack.

shelfInvMissingCond.name: shelfInvMissingCond
shelfInvMissingCond.description: An expansion shelf is missing. To clear this condition, attach an appropriate expansion shelf to the MSCP in the main shelf of the system.

shelfInvMissingClear.name: shelfInvMissingClear
shelfInvMissingClear.description: A previously active shelf missing condition has cleared.

shelfInvUnknownCond.name: shelfInvUnknownCond
shelfInvUnknownCond.description: A shelf is unknown to the system. This condition occurs because the shelf is unknown to the system (for example, the the FRU data cannot be read on the expansion shelf interface (ESI) circuit pack in the expansion shelf). To clear this condition, connect an appropriate shelf to its associated MSCP.

shelfInvUnknownClear.name: shelfInvUnknownClear
shelfInvUnknownClear.description: A previously active shelf unknown condition has cleared.

shelfInvCommCond.name: shelfInvCommCond
shelfInvCommCond.description: This condition indicates that a connected expansion shelf has a communications failure between the multiport system control processor (MSCP) and the expansion shelf interface (ESI) circuit packs.

shelfInvCommClear.name: shelfInvCommClear
shelfInvCommClear.description: A previously active shelf communications condition has cleared.

shelfInvPwrFeedAFailCond.name: shelfInvPwrFeedAFailCond
shelfInvPwrFeedAFailCond.description: There is a power feed A failure. The system can continue to function on power feed B. Plan to diagnose and correct the problem as soon as possible.

shelfInvPwrFeedAFailClear.name: shelfInvPwrFeedAFailClear
shelfInvPwrFeedAFailClear.description: A previously active Power feed A condition has cleared.

shelfInvPwrFeedBFailCond.name: shelfInvPwrFeedBFailCond
shelfInvPwrFeedBFailCond.description: There is a power feed B failure. The system can continue to function on power feed A. Plan to diagnose and correct the problem as soon as possible.

shelfInvPwrFeedBFailClear.name: shelfInvPwrFeedBFailClear
shelfInvPwrFeedBFailClear.description: A previously active Power feed B condition has cleared.

shelfInvPwrBrownoutCond.name: shelfInvPwrBrownoutCond
shelfInvPwrBrownoutCond.description: There is a system power brownout. As voltage levels decrease, the amplifiers fail, followed by the MSCP, and then the cooling unit fails.

shelfInvPwrBrownoutClear.name: shelfInvPwrBrownoutClear
shelfInvPwrBrownoutClear.description: A previously active power brownout condition on the shelf has cleared.

shelfInvSysCommCond.name: shelfInvSysCommCond
shelfInvSysCommCond.description: This condition indicates that backplane communication between the multiport system control processor (MSCP) and the affected circuit pack is interrupted. Normal OAM&P operations to the circuit pack, like provisioning and performance monitoring, are affected while this alarm is active.

shelfInvSysCommClear.name: shelfInvSysCommClear
shelfInvSysCommClear.description: A previously active shelf missing condition has cleared.

shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchCond.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchCond
shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchCond.description: Indicates that the identifying information of the discovered expansion shelf does not match that of the expected shelf.

shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchClear.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchClear
shelfInvExpansionShelfIdMismatchClear.description: A previously active expansion shelf identifier mismatch condition has cleared.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSCond.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSCond
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSCond.description: This alarm indicates that a connected expansion shelf has a loss of signal between the multiport system control processor (MSCP) and the expansion shelf interface (ESI) circuit packs. The most likely causes are a fiber cut or a fault with the Molex connector and cable assembly.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSClear.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSClear
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLOSClear.description: A previously active expansion shelf communications LOS condition has cleared.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownCond.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownCond
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownCond.description: This alarm indicates that a connected expansion shelf has a communications failure between the multiport system control processor (MSCP) and the expansion shelf interface (ESI) circuit packs.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownClear.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownClear
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommLinkDownClear.description: A previously active expansion shelf communications link down condition has cleared.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsuppor.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsupportedCond
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsuppor.description: This alarm indicates that an unknown device is connected to the expansion shelf port of the multiport system control processor (MSCP) on the main shelf.

shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsuppor.name: shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsupportedClear
shelfInvExpansionShelfCommDeviceUnsuppor.description: A previously active expansion shelf communications device unsupported condition has cleared.

shelfInvTempMaxCond.name: shelfInvTempMaxCond
shelfInvTempMaxCond.description: Indicates that the temperature on the identified shelf has risen above the maximum threshold.

shelfInvTempMaxClear.name: shelfInvTempMaxClear
shelfInvTempMaxClear.description: A previously active shelf inventory maximum temperature condition has cleared.

slotInvMissingCond.name: slotInvMissingCond
slotInvMissingCond.description: A Circuit pack is missing. The alarm is triggered for one of the following reasons: the provisioned circuit pack is missing from its associated slot a filler circuit pack is missing from an unprovisioned single-width or doublewidth slot a single-width circuit pack is provisioned in a double-width slot To clear this alarm, insert an appropriate single-width or double-width circuit pack or filler circuit pack in the associated single-width or double-width slot.

slotInvMissingClear.name: slotInvMissingClear
slotInvMissingClear.description: A previously active circuit pack or replaceable unit missing condition has cleared.

slotInvUnknownCond.name: slotInvUnknownCond
slotInvUnknownCond.description: Circuit pack type is unknown to the system. This condition occurs for the following two reasons: the circuit pack in the associated slot is unknown to the system (for example, the circuit pack is not supported by the software release running on the system) two single-width circuit packs are in a double-width slot To clear this condition, insert an appropriate circuit pack in the associated slot.

slotInvUnknownClear.name: slotInvUnknownClear
slotInvUnknownClear.description: A previously active circuit pack or replaceable unit unknown condition has cleared.

slotInvCommCond.name: slotInvCommCond
slotInvCommCond.description: This alarm indicates that backplane communication between the multiport system control processor (MSCP) and the circuit pack is interrupted. Normal OAM&P operations to the circuit pack, like provisioning and performance monitoring, are affected while this alarm is active. If an amplifier or wavelength conversion circuit pack has been provisioned already, it continues to operate normally.

slotInvCommClear.name: slotInvCommClear
slotInvCommClear.description: A previously active circuit pack communications condition has cleared.

slotInvFailCond.name: slotInvFailCond
slotInvFailCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvFailClear.name: slotInvFailClear
slotInvFailClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvUpgradeInProgressCond.name: slotInvUpgradeInProgressCond
slotInvUpgradeInProgressCond.description: A software upgrade process has begun on the circuit pack in the identified slot.

slotInvUpgradeInProgressClear.name: slotInvUpgradeInProgressClear
slotInvUpgradeInProgressClear.description: There is an auto upgrade in progress. This alarm is typically seen when inserting a circuit pack other than a multiport system control processor (MSCP).

slotInvUpgradeFailureCond.name: slotInvUpgradeFailureCond
slotInvUpgradeFailureCond.description: There is a circuit pack upgrade failure.

slotInvUpgradeFailureClear.name: slotInvUpgradeFailureClear
slotInvUpgradeFailureClear.description: A previously active circuit pack software upgrade failure condition has cleared.

slotInvVersionMismatchCond.name: slotInvVersionMismatchCond
slotInvVersionMismatchCond.description: The circuit pack in the indicated slot is running a software version which is inconsistent with the committed software version of the system.

slotInvVersionMismatchClear.name: slotInvVersionMismatchClear
slotInvVersionMismatchClear.description: A previously active circuit pack software version mismatch condition has cleared.

slotInvCoolingUnitFailCond.name: slotInvCoolingUnitFailCond
slotInvCoolingUnitFailCond.description: A cooling unit failure has occurred. One or more fans have failed in the cooling unit.

slotInvCoolingUnitFailClear.name: slotInvCoolingUnitFailClear
slotInvCoolingUnitFailClear.description: A previously active shelf cooling unit failure condition has cleared.

slotInvDspCommCond.name: slotInvDspCommCond
slotInvDspCommCond.description: This alarm indicates that communication has failed either between the DSP and the processor handling backplane communications on an optical amplifier circuit pack, or between the variable optical equalizer (VOE) and the processor handling backplane communications on an active mux/demux circuit pack Normal OAM&P operations to the circuit pack, like provisioning and performance monitoring, is affected when this alarm is active.

slotInvDspCommClear.name: slotInvDspCommClear
slotInvDspCommClear.description: A previously active DSP control communications condition has been cleared.

slotInvUnsupportedPackCond.name: slotInvUnsupportedPackCond
slotInvUnsupportedPackCond.description: A replaceable unit inventory item is unsupported. In this case, a multiport system control processor (MSCP) circuit pack is plugged into any slot of the expansion shelf. However, MSCPs are only supported in slot five of the main shelf.

slotInvUnsupportedPackClear.name: slotInvUnsupportedPackClear
slotInvUnsupportedPackClear.description: A previously active unsupported pack condition has cleared.

slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchCond.name: slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchCond
slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchCond.description: The shelf is plugged in with a wring cooling unit.

slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchClear.name: slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchClear
slotInvCoolingUnitMismatchClear.description: A previously active cooling unit mismatch condition has cleared.

slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailCond.name: slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailCond
slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailClear.name: slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailClear
slotInvPwrFeedAFuseFailClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailCond.name: slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailCond
slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailClear.name: slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailClear
slotInvPwrFeedBFuseFailClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvPowerFailCond.name: slotInvPowerFailCond
slotInvPowerFailCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvPowerFailClear.name: slotInvPowerFailClear
slotInvPowerFailClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownCond.name: slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownCond
slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownClear.name: slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownClear
slotInvHiTempAutoShutdownClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvHTThreshExceededCond.name: slotInvHTThreshExceededCond
slotInvHTThreshExceededCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvHTThreshExceededClear.name: slotInvHTThreshExceededClear
slotInvHTThreshExceededClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvHTSThreshExceededCond.name: slotInvHTSThreshExceededCond
slotInvHTSThreshExceededCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvHTSThreshExceededClear.name: slotInvHTSThreshExceededClear
slotInvHTSThreshExceededClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

slotInvHTASUnsupportedCond.name: slotInvHTASUnsupportedCond
slotInvHTASUnsupportedCond.description: There is a circuit pack failure. The alarm is critical when a circuit pack is provisioned and that it has fails in its associated slot.

slotInvHTASUnsupportedClear.name: slotInvHTASUnsupportedClear
slotInvHTASUnsupportedClear.description: A previously active circuit pack fail condition has cleared.

shelfMismatchCond.name: shelfMismatchCond
shelfMismatchCond.description: The type of the physically detected shelf does not match the provisioned shelf type.

shelfMismatchClear.name: shelfMismatchClear
shelfMismatchClear.description: A previously active shelf type mismatch condition has cleared.

shelfMissingCond.name: shelfMissingCond
shelfMissingCond.description: An expansion shelf is missing. To clear this alarm, attach an appropriate expansion shelf to the MSCP in the main shelf of the system.

shelfMissingClear.name: shelfMissingClear
shelfMissingClear.description: A previously active expansion shelf missing condition has cleared.

shelfConfigurationMismatchCond.name: shelfConfigurationMismatchCond
shelfConfigurationMismatchCond.description: The configuration type of the physically detected expansion shelf does not match the provisioned expansion shelf configuration type.

shelfConfigurationMismatchClear.name: shelfConfigurationMismatchClear
shelfConfigurationMismatchClear.description: A previously active expansion shelf configuration mismatch condition has cleared.

cpMismatchCond.name: cpMismatchCond
cpMismatchCond.description: There is a circuit pack mismatch. There is a mismatch between the equipment provisioned for the slot and the physical circuit pack that is inserted in the slot.

cpMismatchClear.name: cpMismatchClear
cpMismatchClear.description: A previously active circuit pack type mismatch condition has cleared.

cpConnectorMismatchCond.name: cpConnectorMismatchCond
cpConnectorMismatchCond.description: A connector mismatch alarm occurs on a circuit pack that is provisioned with a connector type that is different to the one actually inserted.

cpConnectorMismatchClear.name: cpConnectorMismatchClear
cpConnectorMismatchClear.description: A previously active optical fiber connector type mismatch condition has cleared.

cpInvalidProvCond.name: cpInvalidProvCond
cpInvalidProvCond.description: The type of circuit pack that is provisioned in a slot that is invalid for the shelf slot configuration.

cpInvalidProvClear.name: cpInvalidProvClear
cpInvalidProvClear.description: A previously active invalid circuit pack provisioning condition has cleared.

cpSoftwareBankAFailCond.name: cpSoftwareBankAFailCond
cpSoftwareBankAFailCond.description: There is a hardware failure in software bank A storage device. During this alarm, software backups, upgrades and restores cannot occur. When the MSCP is rebooting, the LEDs on the MSI and the MSCP are lit.

cpSoftwareBankAFailClear.name: cpSoftwareBankAFailClear
cpSoftwareBankAFailClear.description: A previously active software Bank A failure condition has cleared.

cpSoftwareBankBFailCond.name: cpSoftwareBankBFailCond
cpSoftwareBankBFailCond.description: There is a hardware failure in software bank B storage device. During this alarm, software backups, upgrades, and restores cannot occur. When the MSCP is rebooting, the LEDs on the MSI and the MSCP are lit.

cpSoftwareBankBFailClear.name: cpSoftwareBankBFailClear
cpSoftwareBankBFailClear.description: A previously active software Bank B failure condition has cleared.

cpUpgradeInProgressCond.name: cpUpgradeInProgressCond
cpUpgradeInProgressCond.description: Indicates that a system-wide software upgrade process is in progress on the NE.

cpUpgradeInProgressClear.name: cpUpgradeInProgressClear
cpUpgradeInProgressClear.description: A previously active system-wide upgrade in progress condition has cleared.

cpUpgradeFailCond.name: cpUpgradeFailCond
cpUpgradeFailCond.description: Indicates that the system-wide upgrade procedure has failed to complete successfully.

cpUpgradeFailClear.name: cpUpgradeFailClear
cpUpgradeFailClear.description: A previously active circuit pack upgrade failure condition has cleared.

cpDbRestoreInProgressCond.name: cpDbRestoreInProgressCond
cpDbRestoreInProgressCond.description: There is a database restore in progress on the system.

cpDbRestoreInProgressClear.name: cpDbRestoreInProgressClear
cpDbRestoreInProgressClear.description: A previously active NE database restore condition has cleared.

cpDbRecoveryFailCond.name: cpDbRecoveryFailCond
cpDbRecoveryFailCond.description: There is a database recovery failure. If a new MSCP circuit pack fails to acquire the database from the system, a database recovery failure alarm can be triggered after replacing the MSCP.

cpDbRecoveryFailClear.name: cpDbRecoveryFailClear
cpDbRecoveryFailClear.description: A previously active NE database recovery failure condition has cleared.

cpFanFeedFailCond.name: cpFanFeedFailCond
cpFanFeedFailCond.description: A cooling unit feed failure has occurred on a BTI 7030 shelf. There are two cooling unit power feeds from the SCP to the cooling unit. If one power feeds fails, a minor alarm is raised. If both power feed fails, a major alarm is raised.

cpFanFeedFailClear.name: cpFanFeedFailClear
cpFanFeedFailClear.description: A previously active fan power feed failure condition has cleared.

cpStorageCardFailCond.name: cpStorageCardFailCond
cpStorageCardFailCond.description: Indicates that the database storage card has failed.

cpStorageCardFailClear.name: cpStorageCardFailClear
cpStorageCardFailClear.description: A previously active database storage card failure condition has cleared.

cpDbDeletionInProgressCond.name: cpDbDeletionInProgressCond
cpDbDeletionInProgressCond.description: There is a database deletion in progress on the system.

cpDbDeletionInProgressClear.name: cpDbDeletionInProgressClear
cpDbDeletionInProgressClear.description: A previously active NE database deletion condition has cleared.

cpDegradeCond.name: cpDegradeCond
cpDegradeCond.description: Indicates that a failure or degradation has been detected in one or more physical components on the identified circuit pack, which may lead to a failure of the pack to provide service normally.

cpDegradeClear.name: cpDegradeClear
cpDegradeClear.description: A previously active Circuit Pack Degrade condition has cleared.

oaCaseTempCond.name: oaCaseTempCond
oaCaseTempCond.description: A case temperature high threshold is exceeded. A warning is raised to indicate that the amplifier is nearing its shutdown threshold. The circuit pack in the associated slot has exceeded its case temperature high threshold. If the case temperature continues to rise to its shutdown threshold, the circuit pack automatically shuts down.

oaCaseTempClear.name: oaCaseTempClear
oaCaseTempClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier case temperature condition has cleared.

oaCaseTempShutdownCond.name: oaCaseTempShutdownCond
oaCaseTempShutdownCond.description: A case temperature high threshold shutdown has occurred. The optical amplifier is shutdown and taken out-of-service by the system. The pump lasers are turned off and there is no amplification.

oaCaseTempShutdownClear.name: oaCaseTempShutdownClear
oaCaseTempShutdownClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier case temperature shutdown condition has cleared.

oaLaserMinTempShutdownCond.name: oaLaserMinTempShutdownCond
oaLaserMinTempShutdownCond.description: A pump laser temperature low threshold shutdown has occurred. The optical amplifier is shutdown and taken out-of-service by the system.

oaLaserMinTempShutdownClear.name: oaLaserMinTempShutdownClear
oaLaserMinTempShutdownClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier minimum temperature shutdown condition has cleared.

oaLaserMaxTempShutdownCond.name: oaLaserMaxTempShutdownCond
oaLaserMaxTempShutdownCond.description: A pump laser temperature high threshold shutdown has occurred. The optical amplifier is shutdown and taken out-of-service by the system.

oaLaserMaxTempShutdownClear.name: oaLaserMaxTempShutdownClear
oaLaserMaxTempShutdownClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier maximum temperature shutdown condition has cleared.

oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.name: oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond
oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.description: The optical power received (OPR) low threshold is exceeded. The input signal to an optical amplifier has reached the optical power received low threshold. If the input signal drops to below the input sensitivity level, the circuit pack will degrade in performance.

oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.name: oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear
oaOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier minimum power received condition has cleared.

oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.name: oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond
oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.description: The optical power received (OPR) high threshold is crossed. The input signal to an optical amplifier has reached the optical power received high threshold.

oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.name: oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear
oaOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier maximum power received condition has cleared.

oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.name: oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond
oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.description: A second stage input optical power received (OPR) high threshold crossing has occurred.

oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.name: oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear
oaSSIOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier second stage input maximum power received condition has cleared.

oaBackReflectionSafetyCond.name: oaBackReflectionSafetyCond
oaBackReflectionSafetyCond.description: The Optical Back Reflection - High Threshold Safety Override alarm indicates someone has activated the optical power received optical back reflection high threshold safety override (OPR-OBR-HTSO) command to override the automatic power reduction (APR) feature of the amplifier lasers. This command overrides the APR feature of the amplifier for 20 to 600 seconds. When the timer expires, the alarm clears.

oaBackReflectionSafetyClear.name: oaBackReflectionSafetyClear
oaBackReflectionSafetyClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier back reflection safety condition has cleared.

oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond.name: oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond
oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond.description: The optical power transmitted (OPT) low threshold is crossed.

oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear.name: oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear
oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier minimum transmitted power condition has cleared.

oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond.name: oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond
oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond.description: The optical power transmitted (OPT) high threshold has been exceeded on the amplifier.

oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear.name: oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear
oaOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier maximum transmitted power condition has cleared.

oaMSInsertionLossCond.name: oaMSInsertionLossCond
oaMSInsertionLossCond.description: A mid-stage insertion loss high threshold is exceeded for a mid-stage amplifier.

oaMSInsertionLossClear.name: oaMSInsertionLossClear
oaMSInsertionLossClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier midstage insertion loss condition has cleared.

oaAmplifierConditioningCond.name: oaAmplifierConditioningCond
oaAmplifierConditioningCond.description: There is an amplifier conditioning problem. When an amplifier is initially plugged in, thermo-electric coolers (TEC) work to control the pump laser temperature to between 16 degrees and 34 degrees Celsius. Until the pump laser temperature is within range, the amplifier conditioning problem is present. If the amplifier conditioning problem persists for more than 30 minutes, the condition is cleared and either a laser temperature low threshold or a laser temperature high threshold alarm is raised.

oaAmplifierConditioningClear.name: oaAmplifierConditioningClear
oaAmplifierConditioningClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier conditioning condition has cleared.

oaDspCommCond.name: oaDspCommCond
oaDspCommCond.description: This alarm indicates that communication has failed between the DSP and the processor handling backplane communications on an optical amplifier circuit pack. Normal OAM&P operations to the circuit pack, like provisioning and performance monitoring, is affected when this alarm is active.

oaDspCommClear.name: oaDspCommClear
oaDspCommClear.description: A previously active optical amplifier DSP communications condition has cleared.

oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideCond.name: oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideCond
oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideCond.description: The Optical Back Reflection - High Threshold Safety Override alarm indicates someone has activated the high threshold safety override command to override the automatic power reduction (APR) feature of the amplifier lasers. This command overrides the APR feature of the amplifier for 20 to 600 seconds. When the timer expires, the alarm clears.

oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideClear.name: oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideClear
oaBackReflectionSafetyOverrideClear.description: A previously active back reflection safety override condition has been cleared.

oaBackReflectionHighThresholdCond.name: oaBackReflectionHighThresholdCond
oaBackReflectionHighThresholdCond.description: The Optical Amplifier Back Reflection High Threshold alarm indicates that the measured optical back reflection power has exceeded the high threshold. This serves as a warning that optical back reflection is operating at an elevated level, and that continued increases in the optical back reflection level may result in an automatic laser safety shutdown.

oaBackReflectionHighThresholdClear.name: oaBackReflectionHighThresholdClear
oaBackReflectionHighThresholdClear.description: A previously active back reflection high threshold condition has been cleared.

oscLossOfSignalCond.name: oscLossOfSignalCond
oscLossOfSignalCond.description: This condition indicates that an SFP transceiver has experienced an input power drop that is below the manufacturer s preset threshold.

oscLossOfSignalClear.name: oscLossOfSignalClear
oscLossOfSignalClear.description: A previously active optical supervisory channel loss of signal condition has cleared.

oscSfpMissingCond.name: oscSfpMissingCond
oscSfpMissingCond.description: An SFP transceiver is missing from its associated port in an MSCP circuit pack. To clear this alarm, insert an appropriate transceiver in the associated port of the MSCP circuit pack.

oscSfpMissingClear.name: oscSfpMissingClear
oscSfpMissingClear.description: A previously active optical supervisory channel SFP missing condition has cleared.

pluggableInvUnknownCond.name: pluggableInvUnknownCond
pluggableInvUnknownCond.description: The SFP or XFP transceiver type is unknown to the system. This alarm occurs because the transceiver is not supported by the current software. To clear this alarm, insert a readable SFP or XFP transceiver in the associated port of the circuit pack.

pluggableInvUnknownClear.name: pluggableInvUnknownClear
pluggableInvUnknownClear.description: A previously active Pluggable Inventory Unknown condition has cleared.

pluggableInvCommCond.name: pluggableInvCommCond
pluggableInvCommCond.description: This alarm indicates that communication between a circuit pack and an inserted small form factor pluggable (SFP) transceiver is not reliable.

pluggableInvCommClear.name: pluggableInvCommClear
pluggableInvCommClear.description: A previously active Pluggable Inventory communications condition has cleared.

pluggableInvFailCond.name: pluggableInvFailCond
pluggableInvFailCond.description: There is an SFP or XFP transceiver failure.

pluggableInvFailClear.name: pluggableInvFailClear
pluggableInvFailClear.description: A previously active Pluggable Inventory fail condition has cleared.

pluggableInvMismatchCond.name: pluggableInvMismatchCond
pluggableInvMismatchCond.description: There is an SFP mismatch condition active. There is a mismatch between the SFP transceiver provisioned for a port of a circuit pack and the physical SFP transceiver that is inserted in the port.

pluggableInvMismatchClear.name: pluggableInvMismatchClear
pluggableInvMismatchClear.description: A previously active Pluggable Inventory mismatch condition has cleared.

pluggableInvMissingCond.name: pluggableInvMissingCond
pluggableInvMissingCond.description: There is an SFP or XFP missing from the indicated port.

pluggableInvMissingClear.name: pluggableInvMissingClear
pluggableInvMissingClear.description: A previously active Pluggable Inventory missing condition has cleared.

pluggableInvUnsupportedCond.name: pluggableInvUnsupportedCond
pluggableInvUnsupportedCond.description: The electrical SFP transceiver type is NOT supported in the given port. This alarm occurs when an electrical SFP is plugged into a port that does not support GE. To clear this alarm, remove the electrical SFP.

pluggableInvUnsupportedClear.name: pluggableInvUnsupportedClear
pluggableInvUnsupportedClear.description: A previously active Pluggable unsupported condition has cleared.

xcvrMissingCond.name: xcvrMissingCond
xcvrMissingCond.description: An SFP or XFP transceiver is missing from its associated port in a circuit pack.

xcvrMissingClear.name: xcvrMissingClear
xcvrMissingClear.description: A previously active transceiver port missing condition has cleared.

xcvrMismatchCond.name: xcvrMismatchCond
xcvrMismatchCond.description: There is a mismatch between the SFP or XFP transceiver provisioned for a port of a circuit pack and the physical SFP or XFP transceiver that is inserted in the port. The provisioned SFP or XFP transceiver must match the transceiver in the port.

xcvrMismatchClear.name: xcvrMismatchClear
xcvrMismatchClear.description: A previously active transceiver port type mismatch condition has cleared.

xcvrRFICond.name: xcvrRFICond
xcvrRFICond.description: Remote Fault Indication: The source port to which the specified destination transceiver port is cross-connected has a service-affecting fault active against it.

xcvrRFIClear.name: xcvrRFIClear
xcvrRFIClear.description: A previously active transceiver RFI condition has cleared.

xcvrLossOfSignalCond.name: xcvrLossOfSignalCond
xcvrLossOfSignalCond.description: This alarm indicates that an SFP transceiver has experienced an input power drop that is below the preset minimum threshold.

xcvrLossOfSignalClear.name: xcvrLossOfSignalClear
xcvrLossOfSignalClear.description: A previously active transceiver port Loss Of Signal condition has cleared.

xcvrLossOfLockCond.name: xcvrLossOfLockCond
xcvrLossOfLockCond.description: This alarm indicates that a transceiver port is unable to lock on the incoming bit stream. This is a result of either: the provisioned protocol does not match the incoming signal, or the incoming signal is excessively degraded.

xcvrLossOfLockClear.name: xcvrLossOfLockClear
xcvrLossOfLockClear.description: A previously active transceiver port Loss Of Lock condition has cleared.

xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.name: xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond
xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.description: The optical power received (OPR) low threshold is not met. The input signal to a transceiver has reached the optical power received low threshold. If the input signal drops to below the input sensitivity level, the transceiver degrades in performance.

xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.name: xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear
xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.description: A previously active transceiver port minimum power received condition has cleared.

xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.name: xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond
xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.description: The optical power received (OPR) high threshold is exceeded. The input signal to a transceiver has reached the optical power received high threshold.

xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.name: xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear
xcvrOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.description: A previously active transceiver port maximum power received condition has cleared.

xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond.name: xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond
xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinCond.description: The optical power transmitted (OPT) is below the low threshold for the transceiver.

xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear.name: xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear
xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMinClear.description: A previously active transceiver port minimum power transmitted condition has cleared.

xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond.name: xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond
xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxCond.description: The optical power transmitted (OPT) high threshold for a transceiver is exceeded.

xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear.name: xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear
xcvrOpticalPwrTransmittedMaxClear.description: A previously active transceiver port maximum power transmitted condition has cleared.

xcvrLossOfFrameCond.name: xcvrLossOfFrameCond
xcvrLossOfFrameCond.description: A transceiver reports a SONET or SDH loss of frame for a transceiver that is provisioned to receive a SONET or SDH protocol.

xcvrLossOfFrameClear.name: xcvrLossOfFrameClear
xcvrLossOfFrameClear.description: A previously active loss of frame condition has cleared.

xcvrLossOfSyncCond.name: xcvrLossOfSyncCond
xcvrLossOfSyncCond.description: Indicates that a loss of synchronization condition has been detected by the transceiver port on the incoming gigabit ethernet or 10GELAN protocol.

xcvrLossOfSyncClear.name: xcvrLossOfSyncClear
xcvrLossOfSyncClear.description: A previously active loss of synchronization condition has cleared.

xcvrLoopbackCond.name: xcvrLoopbackCond
xcvrLoopbackCond.description: Indicates that the transceiver has been provisioned to enter loopback mode.

xcvrLoopbackClear.name: xcvrLoopbackClear
xcvrLoopbackClear.description: A previously active loopback condition on the transceiver has been cleared.

xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionCond.name: xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionCond
xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionCond.description: The active transceiver of a protected transceiver pair has been forced to switch to the Protection transceiver.

xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionClear.name: xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionClear
xcvrForcedSwitchToProtectionClear.description: A previously active Forced Switch To Protection condition has cleared.

xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingCond.name: xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingCond
xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingCond.description: The active transceiver of a protected transceiver pair has been forced to switch to the Working transceiver.

xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingClear.name: xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingClear
xcvrForcedSwitchToWorkingClear.description: A previously active Forced Switch To Working condition has cleared.

xcvrLockoutProtectionCond.name: xcvrLockoutProtectionCond
xcvrLockoutProtectionCond.description: The Protection transceiver of a protected transceiver pair has been locked out.

xcvrLockoutProtectionClear.name: xcvrLockoutProtectionClear
xcvrLockoutProtectionClear.description: A previously active Lockout Protection condition has cleared.

xcvrLockoutWorkingCond.name: xcvrLockoutWorkingCond
xcvrLockoutWorkingCond.description: The Working transceiver of a protected transceiver pair has been locked out.

xcvrLockoutWorkingClear.name: xcvrLockoutWorkingClear
xcvrLockoutWorkingClear.description: A previously active Lockout Working condition has cleared.

xcvrTempMaxCond.name: xcvrTempMaxCond
xcvrTempMaxCond.description: Indicates that the temperature of the physical transceiver has risen above the maximum threshold.

xcvrTempMaxClear.name: xcvrTempMaxClear
xcvrTempMaxClear.description: A previously active Temperature Exceeded Maximum condition has cleared.

xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableCond.name: xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableCond
xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableCond.description: Indicates that the transceiver is not currently able to tune to the set wavelength.

xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableClear.name: xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableClear
xcvrWavelengthNotAchievableClear.description: A previously active Wavelength Not Achievable condition has cleared.

xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalCond.name: xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalCond
xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalCond.description: An Alarm Indication Signal indication is active on the transceiver port.

xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalClear.name: xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalClear
xcvrAlarmIndicationSignalClear.description: A previously active Alarm Indication Signal condition has cleared.

xcvrTraceMismatchCond.name: xcvrTraceMismatchCond
xcvrTraceMismatchCond.description: This condition indicates that the received trace label on the transciever port does not match the expected trace label.

xcvrTraceMismatchClear.name: xcvrTraceMismatchClear
xcvrTraceMismatchClear.description: A previously active Trace Mismatch condition has cleared.

xcvrRemoteFaultCond.name: xcvrRemoteFaultCond
xcvrRemoteFaultCond.description: A remote fault indication is active on the traceiver port.

xcvrRemoteFaultClear.name: xcvrRemoteFaultClear
xcvrRemoteFaultClear.description: A previously raised remote fault indication has cleared.

xcvrSignalDegradeCond.name: xcvrSignalDegradeCond
xcvrSignalDegradeCond.description: The Signal Degrade BER threshold has been crossed on the transiever port.

xcvrSignalDegradeClear.name: xcvrSignalDegradeClear
xcvrSignalDegradeClear.description: A previously active Signal Degrade condition has cleared.

xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchCond.name: xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchCond
xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchCond.description: An OTN payload mismatch is active on the transceiver port facility.

xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchClear.name: xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchClear
xcvrOTNPayloadMismatchClear.description: A previously active OTN payload mismatch condition on the transceiver port facility has cleared.

xcvrLFCond.name: xcvrLFCond
xcvrLFCond.description: Local Failure: Raised when a port detects and incoming local failure indication is received.

xcvrLFClear.name: xcvrLFClear
xcvrLFClear.description: A previously active transceiver LF condition has cleared.

xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorCond.name: xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorCond
xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorCond.description: An Open Connection Indicator is active on the transceiver port.

xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorClear.name: xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorClear
xcvrOpenConnectionIndicatorClear.description: A previously active Open Connection Indicator condition has cleared.

xcvrReceivedLockoutCond.name: xcvrReceivedLockoutCond
xcvrReceivedLockoutCond.description: A Received Lockout indication is active on the transceiver port.

xcvrReceivedLockoutClear.name: xcvrReceivedLockoutClear
xcvrReceivedLockoutClear.description: A previously active Received Lockout condition has cleared.

xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorCond.name: xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorCond
xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorCond.description: A Backward Defect Indicator is active on the transceiver port.

xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorClear.name: xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorClear
xcvrBackwardDefectIndicatorClear.description: A previously active Backward Defect Indicator condition has cleared.

amdLossOfSignalCond.name: amdLossOfSignalCond
amdLossOfSignalCond.description: This condition indicates that an active mux/demux that has experienced an input power drop that is below the preset threshold. This can be against either a channel or the composite line port.

amdLossOfSignalClear.name: amdLossOfSignalClear
amdLossOfSignalClear.description: A previously raised active multiplexer-demultiplexer loss of signal condition has cleared.

amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.name: amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond
amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinCond.description: Indicates that the input power for the active multiplexer-demultiplexer facility has fallen below the minimum threshold.

amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.name: amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear
amdOpticalPwrReceivedMinClear.description: A previously raised active multiplexer-demultiplexer minimum power received condition has cleared.

amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.name: amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond
amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxCond.description: Indicates that the input power for the active multiplexer-demultiplexer facility has risen above the maximum threshold.

amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.name: amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear
amdOpticalPwrReceivedMaxClear.description: A previously raised active multiplexer-demultiplexer maximum power received condition has cleared.

amdTPLNACond.name: amdTPLNACond
amdTPLNACond.description: A channel target power level not achieved (TPLNA) condition is triggered when the output power for a channel of a 32-Channel DWDM Active Mux/Demux (D32AMD) module is above or below the target power transmitted level for that channel.

amdTPLNAClear.name: amdTPLNAClear
amdTPLNAClear.description: A previously raised active target power level not achieved condition has been cleared.

amdTALNACond.name: amdTALNACond
amdTALNACond.description: The target attenuation level not achieved (TALNA) condition is triggered when the attenuation for a 32-Channel DWDM Active Mux/Demux (D32AMD) is outside the preset attenuation levels for a composite line.

amdTALNAClear.name: amdTALNAClear

dbChangeEvt.name: dbChangeEvt
dbChangeEvt.description: This message indicates that a change has been made in the value of the provisioned object identified by the dbChangeOID Var-Bind. If multiple objects have been changed in the same transaction, there will be multiple occurrances of the dbChangeOID object listed in the Var-Bind list.

dbChangeSecuEvt.name: dbChangeSecuEvt
dbChangeSecuEvt.description: This message indicates that a change has been made in the value of the SNMP community string, SNMP trap reciever, or Tl1User.

pvxLldpRemTablesChangeEvt.name: pvxLldpRemTablesChangeEvt
pvxLldpRemTablesChangeEvt.description: A pvxLldpRemTablesChangeEvt notification is sent when the value of pvxLldpStatsRemTablesLastChangeTime changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to trigger LLDP remote systems table maintenance polls. Note that transmission of lldpRemTablesChange notifications are throttled by the agent. The agent must not generate more than one lldpRemTablesChange notification-event in the indicated period, where a 'notification-event' is the transmission of a single notification PDU type to a list of notification destinations. If additional changes in lldpRemoteSystemsData object groups occur within the indicated throttling period, then these trap- events must be suppressed by the agent. By default the throttling period is set to 10 seconds.
